(55, 'Administration', '', '', 'Apply as special assistant to the CEO-Nigerian Stock Exchange', 'The Nigerian Stock Exchange, services the largest economy in Africa, and\r\n     is championing the development of Africaâ€™s financial markets. The  \r\n   Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing services,  \r\nmarket    data solutions, ancillary technology services, and more. It is\r\n  an   open,  professional and vibrant exchange, connecting Nigeria,  \r\nAfrica and   the  world.<br><br><b><i><u>Job Summary</u></i></b>\r\n<ul><li>The Nigerian Stock Exchange (The Exchange) serves the largest \r\neconomy in Africa, and is championing the development of Africaâ€™s \r\nfinancial markets. </li><li>The Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing \r\nservices, market data solutions, ancillary technology services, and \r\nmore. </li><li>It is an open, professional and vibrant exchange, connecting \r\nNigeria, Africa and the world. The Special Assistant (SA) will provide \r\nexecutive support to the CEO of the Exchange. </li><li>The job holder will also be the primary point of contact for \r\ninternal and external constituencies on all matters pertaining to the \r\nOffice of the CEO.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>\r\nKey Responsibilities\r\n<ul><li>Oversees a broad variety of administrative tasks for the CEO \r\nincluding: composing and preparing correspondence, arranging complex and\r\n detailed travel plans, itineraries, and agendas</li><li>Provides support for the CEO regarding advocacy with the \r\nGovernment (Executive, Legislative and Judiciary at the federal, state \r\nand local government levels) on various market friendly policies</li><li>Provides support in preparation for internal and external \r\nmeetings; attend meetings and follow-up on meeting action points on \r\nbehalf of the CEO (within and outside the country)</li><li>Provides members of the Executive Management team leverage in \r\nmoving projects forward by assisting with information gathering, \r\ncommunicating with different parties, developing and monitoring plans, \r\nkeeping track of responsibilities etc. Provides a bridge for smooth \r\ncommunication between the Office of the CEO and departments; \r\ndemonstrating leadership to maintain credibility, trust and support with\r\n senior management staff</li><li>Drafts and disseminate correspondence including letters, memos and emails</li><li>Prepares briefings for meetings, conferences, press appearances, etc</li><li>Manages special projects assigned by the CEO</li><li>Maintains confidentiality on all work issues and opportunities</li></ul><br>', '<br><b><i><u>Qualifications and Experience</u></i></b><br>\r\n<ul><li>A degree in Business Administration or a related field</li><li>Minimum of 10 yearsâ€™ relevant experience in a dynamic, fast-paced environment. </li></ul>\r\n<b><i><u>Functional Competencies</u></i></b><br>\r\n<ul><li>Analytical Thinking</li><li>Client Relationship Management</li><li>Conflict Management</li><li>Data Management</li><li>Documents/Records Management</li><li>Ethics Knowledge</li><li>Government &amp; Media Relations</li><li>Information Management</li><li>Networking</li><li>Project Management</li><li>Microsoft Office Packages&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul>\r\n<b><i><u>Behavioural Competencies\r\n</u></i></b><ul><li>Attention to Detail</li><li>Building Trust</li><li>Collaboration</li><li>Decision Making</li><li>Effective Communication Skills (Written &amp; Oral)</li><li>Emotional Intelligence</li><li>Influence</li><li>Inter-Personal Relations</li><li>Leadership</li><li>Planning and Organizing</li><li>Result Oriented</li><li>Time Management &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </li></ul>\r\nApplication Closing Date<br>\r\n16th February, 2018.<br><br>Apply through the link below<br><br><a href="https://www.nse.com.ng:8443/careers/#/vacancy/54" target="" rel="">https://www.nse.com.ng:8443/careers/#/vacancy/54</a><br><br><br><br><br>', 'Lagos', '', '', '', 8, 'February 13, 2018'),
(56, '', '', '', 'Various positions at Admiralty University of Nigeria', 'The Admiralty University of Nigeria is seeking to recruit dynamic and \r\nhigh calibre professionals for a number of academic and administrative \r\npositions. Applications are invited from suitably qualified candidates \r\nto fill Full-Time, Part-Time and Daily Part-Time vacancies in the \r\nfollowing Academic Departments of the University:<br>', 'check more at<br><a href="http://adun.edu.ng/vacancies/vacancies-administrative/" target="" rel="">http://adun.edu.ng/vacancies/vacancies-administrative/</a><br><br>', '', '', '', '', 9, 'February 13, 2018'),
(57, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Vacancy for Experienced accountant at MVDG Ltd', ' Well trained and experience Marketer (Anthony Mainland). With minimum of HND/BSC.\r\n A Qualified and experience Accountant ( Anthony Mainland). With a  minimum of HND/BSC.\r\n\r\nInterested applicants should forward their  C.V to\r\nInfo.mvdgsolutionsltd@gmail.com \r\nOR \r\nCall: 08160995230,\r\n08146307950\r\nMVDG Solutions Ltd\r\nRoad 2, Suite C-264 Ikota Business Complex VGC Lekki, Lagos.', '\r\nCall: 08160995230,\r\n08146307950\r\nMVDG Solutions Ltd\r\nRoad 2, Suite C-264 Ikota Business Complex VGC Lekki, Lagos.', 'Lagos', '', '', '', 6, 'February 15, 2018'),
(58, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of General Manager', '&nbsp;Vacancy for the position of General Manager<br><br><b><i><u>Job Qualifications</u></i></b>: <br>â€¢Bachelorsâ€™ degree required. Masterâ€™s Degree in Business Administration would be an added advantage. <br>â€¢ A minimum of 5 years of experience with the last 2 years of experience in a leadership capacity required. <br>â€¢Advanced MS skills. <br>â€¢Desire to work as part of a team and willingness to promote the principles and views of the organization. <br>â€¢Ability to work with minimal supervision â€“ self-motivated &amp; confident. â€¢Ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously. <br><br>â€¢Ability to effectively address and solve problems and make decisions in a manner consistent with the companyâ€™s core values and objectives. <br><br>â€¢Confident public speaking and able to express ideas verbally and in writing. Male Preferably&nbsp;', 'Interested and qualified applicants should kindly forward their Cvs to&nbsp;<a target="_blank" rel="">consulting@hcdclimited.com</a>.', '', '', '', '', 4, 'February 15, 2018'),
(60, 'IT and Communication', '', '', 'testing work', '', '<p><strong>Register:</strong> is a small set of data holding places that are part of the computer processor. A <em>register</em> may hold an instruction, a storage address, or any kind of data (such as a bit sequence or individual characters). Some instructions specify <em>registers</em> as part of the instruction.<em>&nbsp;Registers</em> usually consist of a small amount of fast storage, although some <em>registers</em> have specific hardware functions, and may be read-only or write-only. Examples are AC or Accumulator, Data <em>Register</em> or DR, the AR or Address <em>Register</em>, <em>program</em> counter (PC), Memory Data <em>Register</em> (MDR) ,Index <em>register,&nbsp;</em>Memory Buffer <em>Register.</em></p><p><em><strong>System Software:&nbsp;</strong></em>is a variety of software that support the operation of a computer. They are design to run on computer application software and hardware. Examples include operating <em>systems</em>, computational science <em>software</em>, game engines, industrial automation, and <em>software</em> as service applications.</p><p><strong>Operating System:</strong> is a software that control the whole activity of a computer. It manages the computer hardware and software resources and provide a common services for the computer program. Without the <em>operating system</em>, a computer and software programs would be useless. Example are Windows XP, Windows Vista, 8, 10, LINUX, Ubuntu etc</p><p><br></p>', 'Abuja', '', 'test@h.com', '', 7, 'February 17, 2018'),
(61, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for a Procurement officer', '', '<div dir="auto">A construction company on the island urgently needs a ;</div><div dir="auto">1. PA to MD preferably an administrator&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">2. Procurement officer ( lady) with an engineering background&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">3. A Brand Manager with 5 to 10 years experience</div><p><br></p><p>Please send cvs to <a href="mailto:immoneke@slava-bogu.com" target="_blank">immoneke@slava-bogu.com</a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'immoneke@slava-bogu.com', '', 2, 'February 19, 2018'),
(62, 'Marketing', '', '', '100 Direct sales agents needed for a financial institute.', '', '<div dir="auto"><strong><em>Direct sales agents needed for a financial institute.</em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Job Requirements-&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Applicant&nbsp; must be 26 years and below</div><div dir="auto">Must have completed Nysc</div><div dir="auto">2nd class lower only</div><div dir="auto">Degree holders only&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">no HND no ND</div><div dir="auto">Salary-N48,500 + commission</div><div dir="auto">If you are interested please come with the following.</div><div dir="auto">Original waec,nysc cert,birth certificate and degrees cert.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Office Address-44 jimoh odutola ,blk h off Eric Moore surulere</div><div dir="auto">N.B 100 candidates needed</div>', 'Lagos', '', '', '', 3, 'February 19, 2018'),
(63, 'Marketing', '', '', '100 Direct sales agents needed for a financial institute.', '', '<div dir="auto"><strong><em>Direct sales agents needed for a financial institute.</em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Job Requirements-&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Applicant&nbsp; must be 26 years and below</div><div dir="auto">Must have completed Nysc</div><div dir="auto">2nd class lower only</div><div dir="auto">Degree holders only&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">no HND no ND</div><div dir="auto">Salary-N48,500 + commission</div><div dir="auto">If you are interested please come with the following.</div><div dir="auto">Original waec,nysc cert,birth certificate and degrees cert.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Office Address-44 jimoh odutola ,blk h off Eric Moore surulere</div><div dir="auto">N.B 100 candidates needed</div>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjobz@gmail.com', '', 2, 'February 19, 2018'),
(64, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Vacancy for Direct Sales Agent in a reputable bank', '', '<div dir="auto">A reputable bank is in need of Direct Sales Agent, Department of Business Development.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">The Direct Sales Executive plays a key role in communicating and promoting the</div><div dir="auto">bank&rsquo;s products to new and existing customers and also canvassing markets for new products.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><strong><u>Specific Responsibilities:</u></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Selling loans and all other bank&rsquo;s products to customers</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Evaluating loan applications and documentations</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;Identifying cross-selling opportunities</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;Participating in company-wide market storms/strategies</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><u><strong>Job Qualifications</strong></u></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">BSc/HND in relevant discipline</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Must have completed NYSC or have an exemption letter</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;0-3 years&rsquo; work experience</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Skill Requirements</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Excellent communication skills</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ability to close sales</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Passionate about sales and Persistent</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Problem solving skills</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Good analytical skills</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Salary :Annual gross of &nbsp;NGN720,000 (base salary) + sales commission</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Preferred Location : Island/mainland</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Interested candidate should send in their CVs to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:recruitment@5thquadrant.net" target="_blank">recruitment@5thquadrant.net</a>&nbsp; before today 4pm, Monday 19th February 2018.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Please note that the interview is tomorrow.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Also indicate what time would be suitable for you for the interview tomorrow between (10am, 12noon &amp; 2pm)</div>', 'Lagos', '', 'recruitment@5thquadrant.net', '', 3, 'February 19, 2018'),
(65, 'Call Centre', '', '', 'Vacancy for a Customer Experience Manager', '', '<div dir="auto">A reputable company is need of a Customer Experience Manager.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Applicant Must have a minimum of 1 year experience in digital marketing on &nbsp;social media platforms</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Must reside around ikeja *area*&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Either male or female</div><div dir="auto">Quick learner</div><div dir="auto">Good use of initiative Possess leadership skills</div><div dir="auto">Result oriented person&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Creative content writer</div><div dir="auto">Able to work with little or no supervision</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Doesn&#39;t mind working on shift (Night Shift Inclusive)*</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Salary: *50,000*&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Interested candidates should send their cvs to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hr@chukwudohgroup.com" target="_blank">hr@chukwudohgroup.com</a> before 4pm, 20th of February 2018.</div>', 'Lagos', '', 'hr@chukwudohgroup.com', '', 3, 'February 19, 2018'),
(66, 'Accounting', '', '', ' Vacancy for the Position of Accountant at Donmax Consulting Limited', '', '<p>&nbsp;Accountant needed at Donmax Consulting Limited<br>N85,000 - N125,000.<br>Closing Date<br>2nd March, 2018.<br><br>Interested and qualified candidates should forward their CV&#39;s to: hr@donmaxconsulting.com.ng<br><br><br></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'hr@donmaxconsulting.com.ng', '', 6, 'February 19, 2018'),
(67, 'Technician', '', '', 'Executive Drivers needed at Eden Care & Resourcing Limited', '', '<p>Executive Drivers needed &nbsp;at Eden Care &amp; Resourcing Limited<br><br>Qualification Secondary School (SSCE) &nbsp;<br>Experience 10 years<br>Location Lagos<br><br>Location: Ikoyi &amp; Ikeja<br>Accommodation would be provided by client<br>Pay range: #70,000 #80,000 per month<br><br>CVs to careers@edencarelimited.com</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'careers@edencarelimited.com', '', 3, 'February 19, 2018'),
(68, 'IT and Communication', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of DATACOM ENGINEER -deadline is Friday March 2nd', '', '<p>Mactay consulting Advertised the POSITION OF DATACOM ENGINEER</p><p><strong><em><u>JOB REQUIREMENTS</u></em></strong></p><p>1.at least 3 year work experience in Datacom area.</p><p>2. experience of IP network design, implementation, troubleshooting, management;</p><p>3. good knowledge about router-protocol, include OSPF,ISIS,BGP;</p><p>4. good knowledge about LAN technology, include VLAN,STP,TRUNK;</p><p>5. WLAN/GPON knowledge or experience is better;</p><p>6.knowledge basic network security is better;</p><p>7.Huawei certified or the same class certified is better</p><p>Interested applicants must have B.SC in Computer Science /Computer Engineering with 3 years experience</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>APPLICATION</p><p>Interested applicants should send their cv to recruitment@mactayconsulting.com</p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'recruitment@mactayconsulting.com', '', 4, 'February 22, 2018'),
(69, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for Branch Head of Operations in a logistics firm', '', '<p>An experienced hand is required for employment in a logistics firm as Branch Head of Operations. To handle logistics, procurements and facilities (human and material) management. KPIs include but not limited to data analysis and representation with Office suites, reporting, resource management ,driving and negotiating skills, ability to drive , coordinate support staff and flexibility in availability for out of station work is an added advantage.&nbsp;</p><p>Qualification HND/BSc.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>Kindly contact call/message or chat 08024307980 for more details. <a href="mailto:Info.Dcubeconsulting@gmail.com" target="_blank">Info.Dcubeconsulting@gmail.com</a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'Info.Dcubeconsulting@gmail.com', '', 4, 'February 23, 2018'),
(70, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Medical sales Executive at Oakleaf Pharmaceuticals Limited ', '', '<div dir="auto">Oakleaf Pharmaceuticals Limited requires the services of a 2 young, dynamic, Ready to learn, team players for the role of a Medical sales executive. Requirements are at least a HND or Diploma from a recognised educational institution.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;Interested candidates should send their cv&#39;s names and contact details of 2 referees on or before 25 February, 2018 to <a href="mailto:hrtapster@gmail.com" target="_blank">hrtapster@gmail.com</a>&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Please note only SHORTLISTED candidates would be contacted&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Thanks</div>', 'Lagos', '', 'hrtapster@gmail.com', '', 3, 'February 23, 2018'),
(71, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of an ACCOUNTANT -Abuja', '', '<p><strong><u>JOB ROLE</u></strong></p><p>1. Verify, allocate, post and reconcile accounts payable and receivable&nbsp;</p><p>2. Review and recommend modifications to accounting systems and procedures&nbsp;</p><p>3. Fixed asset accounting including proper accounting and physical verification of assets&nbsp;</p><p>4. Participate in budgeting and forecasting process&nbsp;</p><p>5. Assist with tax audits and tax returns&nbsp;</p><p>6. Coordinate internal and external audits &nbsp;</p><p>7. Ensure compliance with GAAP principles&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Requirements</u></strong>&nbsp;</p><p>Qualified Chartered Accountant from ICAN or equivalent Qualification&nbsp;</p><p>In-depth understanding of Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP)&nbsp;</p><p>Proficiency in Excel,Word,Vlookups and pivot tables,Powerpoint is Mandatory &nbsp;</p><p>Exposure in ERP(Specifically in Dynamics) will have added advantage *8-10 Years Experience as an ACCOUNTANT&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>Candidate must have sound knowledge on TAX &nbsp;management &nbsp;</p><p>Applicant must be able to build and manage smooth relationship&nbsp;</p><p>Candidate must have knowledge of FIRS&nbsp;</p><p>Professionalism,<wbr>dependability,integrity and trustworthiness combined with a coorporative attitude&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>DEADLINE:27th February,2018 APPLICANT MUST BE RESIDENT OF ABUJA Qualified candidate should forward updated CV to: jobs@lorachegroups or <a href="mailto:lorachejobs@gmail.com" target="_blank">lorachejobs@gmail.com</a> using position applied for as subject of the mail</p>', 'Abuja', '', 'jobs@lorachegroups', '', 5, 'February 23, 2018'),
(72, 'Administration', '', '', ' SALES/MARKETING Positions at CUSTODIAN LIFE ASSURANCE LIMITED', '', '<div dir="auto">Recruitment is ongoing at CUSTODIAN LIFE ASSURANCE LIMITED &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">HND/Bsc in any discipline. .</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Remuneration is Attractive</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Welfare package available</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Allowance for Transportation</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Pension Scheme</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Group Life/Group personal Accident (GPA)</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Promotion await outstanding performance</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*13th month Bonus</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Conducive Environment</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">*Continuous &nbsp;Sales Training</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Position: SALES/MARKETING</div><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><div dir="auto">Interested Candidate should forward their CV to <a href="mailto:sfngrecruitment@gmail.com" target="_blank">sfngrecruitment@gmail.com</a></div>', 'Lagos', '', 'sfngrecruitment@gmail.com', '', 12, 'February 27, 2018'),
(73, 'Technician', '', '', 'Vacancy for Field Service Representative', '', '<div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job Description</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">We are looking for a motivated Field Service Representative that can work with little direction to ensure the high quality of customer service.</div><div dir="auto">The goal is to maximize customer commitment and the prosperity of business by producing results in a timely manner.</div><div dir="auto"><strong><em>Responsibilities</em></strong></div><div dir="auto">Undertake all customer support tasks in external facilities</div><div dir="auto">Operate efficiently to conclude all on site installation, repair, maintenance and test activities</div><div dir="auto">Guarantee that the work progress accurately follows the agenda</div><div dir="auto">Perform troubleshooting and strive to resolve issues</div><div dir="auto">Produce frequent and analytical service reports</div><div dir="auto">Operate vehicle in a safely manner and use field automation systems</div><div dir="auto">Adhere to company&rsquo;s given rules and regulations</div><div dir="auto">Team up with colleagues and pass on important information</div><div dir="auto">Discern customer needs and offer advice or recommendations</div><div dir="auto">Formulate relationships of trust with customers</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job Requirements</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto">Proven experience as a field service representative</div><div dir="auto">Ability to manage and preserve technical equipment</div><div dir="auto">Good knowledge of english</div><div dir="auto">Ability to easily acclimate to modified schedules and shifts</div><div dir="auto">Accustomed to using mobile tools and applications</div><div dir="auto">Technical degree or certification</div><div dir="auto">Minimum of HND in Engineering field</div><div dir="auto">Salary</div><div dir="auto">N180,000 - N250,000 monthly</div><div dir="auto">Application Closing Date</div><div dir="auto">16th March, 2018</div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Method of Application</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto">Interested and qualified candidate should send their CV&#39;s to: <a href="mailto:hr@leedtecengineering.com.ng" target="_blank">hr@leedtecengineering.com.ng</a></div>', 'Lagos', '', 'hr@leedtecengineering.com.ng', '', 17, 'February 27, 2018'),
(74, 'Oil and Gas', '', '', 'Trainee Field Engineer at  a reputable oil and gas drilling company in Port Harcourt', '', '<div dir="auto">&nbsp;A reputable oil and gas drilling company in Port Harcourt is seeking a qualified candidate for the position below:</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Job Title: Trainee Field Engineer</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job Requirements</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Interested candidate MUST possess a minimum of B.Eng. or B.Sc. (2nd Class Lower) in Electrical/Electronic Engineering or Mechanical Engineering or Electrical Engineering or Petroleum Engineering or GeologyCandidates must have also completed their one (1) year NYSC programme.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Application Closing Date</div><div dir="auto">15th March, 2018.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">How to Apply</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Interested and qualified candidates should send in their written applications, cover letter and CV&rsquo;s to: The Human Resources Manager, P.O Box 5873. Port Harcourt, Rivers State.</div>', 'Port Harcourt', '', 'myhotjobz@gmail.com', '', 7, 'February 27, 2018'),
(75, 'Medicals', '', '', 'Apply as Chemical Pathologist at NIGERIAN Navy', '', '<p>The <a href="http://www.hotnigerianjobs.com/company/nigeria-navy/" target="_blank">Nigeria Navy</a> - invites applications from suitably qualified</p><p>The&nbsp;<a href="http://www.hotnigerianjobs.com/company/nigeria-navy/" target="_blank">Nigeria Navy</a> - invites applications from suitably qualified Nigerians who are desirous of enlistment as Medical Consultants into the Nigerian Navy Direct Short Service Commission (DSSC) Course 25 in the under-listed position below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title:&nbsp;</strong><strong>Chemical Pathologist<br></strong></p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Nationwide&nbsp;</p><p>Department: Medicine&nbsp;</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Entry Qualifications</strong></p><p>Applicants are to possess:</p><ul><li>Fellowship of West African Colleges or National Medical Colleges in the respective specialization such as FWACS, FWACO, FMCOG or equivalents obtained from foreign institutions.</li><li>Certificate or Registration with the Medical and Dental Council of Nigeria.</li><li>Certificate of Registration of Additional Certificates.</li><li>All other relevant certificates.</li></ul><p><strong>General Instructions</strong></p><ul><li>Applicants who obtained credentials from foreign institutions should ensure that the certificates are authenticated by the Federal Ministry of Education.</li><li>Applicants must possess NYSC Discharge Certificate or letter of exemption from NYSC.</li><li>Applicants must possess the National ID Card or National ID Card Acknowledgment slip.</li><li>Male applicants must not be less than 1.65 metres tall while female applicants must not be less than 1.62 metres tall.</li><li>Applicants should be between 35 and 40 years of age by 31st March, 2018.</li><li>Applicants will be shortlisted for a screening interview. The date and time of the interview will be communicated via this website.</li><li>Applicants are warned against giving false information or tendering fake certificates. Any false information or fake certificates discovered, at any stage will lead to disqualification and subsequent prosecution of the applicant.</li><li>Applicants are to print out the documents on successful completion of the online application process.</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>29th March, 2018.</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="http://nnr.azurewebsites.net/Account/Register" target="_blank"><strong>Click Here to Register Online</strong></a></p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Entry Qualifications</strong></p><p>Applicants are to possess:</p><ul><li>Fellowship of West African Colleges or National Medical Colleges in the respective specialization such as FWACS, FWACO, FMCOG or equivalents obtained from foreign institutions.</li><li>Certificate or Registration with the Medical and Dental Council of Nigeria.</li><li>Certificate of Registration of Additional Certificates.</li><li>All other relevant certificates.</li></ul><p><strong>General Instructions</strong></p><ul><li>Applicants who obtained credentials from foreign institutions should ensure that the certificates are authenticated by the Federal Ministry of Education.</li><li>Applicants must possess NYSC Discharge Certificate or letter of exemption from NYSC.</li><li>Applicants must possess the National ID Card or National ID Card Acknowledgment slip.</li><li>Male applicants must not be less than 1.65 metres tall while female applicants must not be less than 1.62 metres tall.</li><li>Applicants should be between 35 and 40 years of age by 31st March, 2018.</li><li>Applicants will be shortlisted for a screening interview. The date and time of the interview will be communicated via this website.</li><li>Applicants are warned against giving false information or tendering fake certificates. Any false information or fake certificates discovered, at any stage will lead to disqualification and subsequent prosecution of the applicant.</li><li>Applicants are to print out the documents on successful completion of the online application process.</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>29th March, 2018.</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="http://nnr.azurewebsites.net/Account/Register" target="_blank"><strong>Click Here to Register Online</strong></a></p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 2, 'February 27, 2018'),
(76, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Internal Auditor for God is Good Motors', '', '<p>We are currently looking to fill the Internal Auditor role for GIGM *(Asaba, Iyana Ipaja, Utako &amp; Uselu)*.<br><br>The Internal Auditor will be responsible for monitoring the effective management of the company&rsquo;s funds and assets; ensuring the improvement of internal processes for finding and eliminating waste and fraud. &nbsp;<br><br>Interested candidates should forward a customized cover letter and CV to jobs@thegiggroupng.com<br><br>Subject of mail: Internal Auditor (Indicate location)<br><br>Note the deadline for application is 7th March, 2018.<br><br>*If you believe you have what it takes to work in a dynamic and an unconventional transportation company...... We want you!!!*</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'jobs@thegiggroupng.com', '', 4, 'February 27, 2018'),
(77, 'Teaching', '', '', 'Vacancy for  Female English tutors/Editors and classroom teachers at The Professionals Schools, Onitshc', '', '<div dir="auto">The Professionals Schools is a Nigeria-British Curriculum School located in Onitsha, Nigeria. The school is a centre of academic excellence, in a purpose built campus with state of the art facilities. The Professionals Schools is a highly selective, co-educational day Primary School which prepares students for the CIE, IGCSE examinations.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Applications are welcome from energetic, adaptable, enthusiastic and experienced Female English tutors/Editors and classroom teachers/School Administrator, with at least 5years experience in administration in a school environment. A generous package is available which includes, excellent salary package, annual travel,basic allowances etc The school is seeking the following staff for September 2018/2019 session.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><u>Qualification:&nbsp;</u></strong>B.A(ed) /B.sc/M.Sc &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Experience required: Only candidates with &nbsp;experience in teaching Nigeria-British Curriculum and IGCSE should apply. Candidates for these posts must be Females with qualified teacher status, have completed at least three years classroom experience, and have a positive outlook.Applications should include a letter of application, curriculum vitae and the names and email contacts of three referees . You should include key aspects of your previous experience (teaching and non-teaching). Please include your date of birth, nationality, marital status and details of any dependent children</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Location: Onitsha- Nigeria</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><div dir="auto">Applications Should Be Emailed To</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><a href="mailto:theprofessionalsschools@gmail.com" target="_blank">theprofessionalsschools@gmail.<wbr>com</a></div><div dir="auto">Successful applicants will be shortlisted two weeks before the interview.</div><div dir="auto">Interview will be held in Onitsha, Enugu and PortHarcourt on 12th April 2018. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Contact: 08059599373(SMS only)</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Closing Date: 14th March, 2018</div>', 'Nigeria', '', 'theprofessionalsschools@gmail.com', '', 2, 'February 28, 2018'),
(78, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Vacancy for Outlet Manager at Montaigne Place', '', '<div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Montaigne Place is Nigeria&#39;s largest luxury skincare, cosmetic, fragrance, and well-being retail company. Founded on the vision to provide luxury at its best, Montaigne Place provides an exceptional sophisticated shopping experience with our exclusive offers. Montaigne Place currently has luxury retail outlets across Nigeria. Our brand&#39;s portfolio cuts across different categories.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Outlet Manager</div><div dir="auto">Job TypeFull Time &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">QualificationBA/BSc/HND &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Experience 3 - 5 years</div><div dir="auto">Location Lagos</div><div dir="auto">Job Field Sales / Marketing / Business Development &nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Location: Lagos Island</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">The Outlet Manager is saddled with the responsibility of increasing the outlet turnover and maximize profitability.</div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job Brief</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Do you have the ability to promote and increase sales through the outlets?</div><div dir="auto">Are you willing to improve customer loyalty and satisfaction?</div><div dir="auto">Can you ensure customer satisfaction, stock management and also cash management?</div><div dir="auto">If you think you can add a lot to Montaigne Place then we are seeking to recruit a dynamic, vibrant, passionate and aggressive individual like you to fill this role.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job Description</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Promote and increase sales through the outlets</div><div dir="auto">Improve customer loyalty and satisfaction</div><div dir="auto">Ensure customer satisfaction</div><div dir="auto">Stock management</div><div dir="auto">Drive promotional activities</div><div dir="auto">Cash management</div><div dir="auto">Maximize profitability</div><div dir="auto">Requirements</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Candidate must be male and SMART</div><div dir="auto">Minimum of an HND or B.Sc in any relevant discipline</div><div dir="auto">3 - 5 years post-NYSC experience in as a Sales Manager, Marketing, Customer Service or Business Development</div><div dir="auto">Experience in the retail environment is very crucial and an added advantage</div><div dir="auto">Should have good administrative skills.</div><div dir="auto">Only residents on the Island will be considered.</div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Method of Application</div><div dir="auto">Applicants should send their Resumes to: <a href="mailto:hrexecutive@montaigneplace.com" target="_blank">hrexecutive@montaigneplace.com</a></div>', 'Lagos', '', 'hrexecutive@montaigneplace.com', '', 11, 'February 28, 2018'),
(79, 'Medicals', '', '', 'Vacancy for Part-time Consultant Cardiologist and Part-time Histopathologist', '', '<div dir="auto">Available openings in a State-of-the-art Healthcare facility in the heart of Ajah in Lagos state.</div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto">Available positions:</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">1. Part-time Consultant Cardiologist - Minimum 2 years&rsquo; post-fellowship experience and highly skilled in echocardiography and ECG.&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">2. Part-time Histopathologist - minimum two years&#39; working experience especially in a high throughput centre.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Full registration and affiliation with relevant professional bodies required for both positions.&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><u>Please note candidates within VI, Lekki and Ajah environs will be given utmost preference due to facility location</u></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">All interested candidates should mail their CV&#39;s to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:career@wellmedhealthcareltd.com" target="_blank">career@wellmedhealthcareltd.<wbr>com</a></div>', 'Lagos', '', 'career@wellmedhealthcareltd.com', '', 9, 'February 28, 2018'),
(80, 'Consulting', '', '', 'CONSULTANTS VACANCIES AT ECOWAS (more than 100 positions)', '', '<p>Ecowas is recruiting!<br><br><br>The Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) is a regional group of fifteen West African countries. Founded on 28 May 1975, with the signing of the Treaty of Lagos, its mission is to promote economic integration across the region.<br><br>The ECOWAS Commission wishes to update its data base of Consultants as part of the preparation for the implementation of for the years 2018 &amp; 2019.<br><br>The ECOWAS Commission hereby invites reputable qualified consultants (firms or individuals) with vast experience and expertise in the following fields below to apply for the registration exercise:<br><br>1.)&nbsp;Consultant (Industry &amp; Private Sector)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>2.)&nbsp;Consultant (Strategic Planning / Strategic Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>3.)&nbsp;Consultant (Human Resources)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>4.) Consultant (Early Warning and Response)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>5.)&nbsp;Consultant (Legal Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>6.)&nbsp;Consultant (Telecommunications)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>7.) Consultant (Information Technologies (IT))<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br>8.) Consultant (Multilateral Surveillance)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>9.) Consultant (Trade and Customs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>10.) Consultant (Free Movement)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>11.) Consultant (Peace and Security)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>12.) Consultant (Political Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April,<br><br><br>13.)&nbsp;Consultant (Microeconomics Policy)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>14.) Consultant (Monitoring and Evaluation)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>15.)&nbsp;Consultant (Environment Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>16.)&nbsp;Consultant (Mining)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>17.) Consultant (External Relations)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April,<br><br><br>18.)&nbsp;Consultant (Youth &amp; Sports Development)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>19.)&nbsp;Consultant (Health)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>20.) Consultant (Culture and Tourism)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>21.) Consultant (Communications and Journalism)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>22.)&nbsp;Consultant (Quality Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>23.) Consultant (Administration)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>24.) Consultant (Education)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>25.) Consultant (Gender)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>26.)&nbsp;Consultant (Humanitarian &amp; Social Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>27.)&nbsp;Consultant (Infrastructures)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>28.)&nbsp;Consultant (Energy)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>29.)&nbsp;Consultant (Agriculture)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>30.) Consultant (Research &amp; Statistics)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>31.)&nbsp;Consultant (Economics)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>32.)&nbsp;Consultant (Audits)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>33.)&nbsp;Individual Consultant (Mid-term Evaluation (MTE) of SIDA&#39;s Support)<br><br>Deadline: 29th March, 2018.<br><br><br><br>34.) Consultant (Recruitment Services)<br><br>Deadline: 26th March, 2018.<br>Method of Application<br>Interested and qualified candidates/firms should send their Expressions of Interest to the address below and clearly marked: &ldquo;Expression of Interest for Registration as Consultant for ECOWAS Commission&rdquo;, Do not open, except in presence of the ECOWAS Procurement Committee:<br>Commissioner General Administration &amp; Conference,<br>ECOWAS Commission,<br>No. 101 Yakubu Gowon Crescent,<br>Asokoro,<br>Abuja.<br><br>Please clearly indicate on the envelope as well as in the covering letter if your submission is for Individual, Consultant or Firm Consultant.<br><br>The Expression of Interest must be submitted in the following order:<br>Cover Letter duly signed by the firm&rsquo;s authorized signatory indicating the area of specialization;<br>Company Profile;<br>Certificate of Incorporation / Registration with the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC);<br>Certified True Copy of Tax Clearance Certificate for the years (2016; 2015 and 2014)<br>Evidence of financial capacity (Certified True Copy of Audited financial statement for the years (2016; 2015 and 2014);<br>CV&rsquo;s of Personnel (copy of all Certificates/Degrees presented)<br>Three (3) verifiable job completion certificate(s) (in the indicated area of interest) executed within the last ten (10) years from 2017;<br>Exact location and full addresses/contact telephone numbers / Email address<br>An Expression of Interest shall be disqualified where any of the above listed documentations is not provided and any job completion certificates submitted by any consultant (firm) must have verifiable and functional address / email and phone number of the client issuing the certificate.<br>Expressions of Interest shall be submitted (1 Original + 3 Copies) in a sealed envelope indicating the name of the consultant (firms or individuals); specific area of specialization.<br>An Expression of Interest shall be disqualified where no specific area of specialization is indicated on the envelope as well as in the cover letter A firm or individual cannot apply for more than three (3) areas of specialization.<br>Note<br>Electronic submissions are not accepted and will therefore not be considered.<br>Interested suppliers / contractors or service providers can obtain further information at the e-mail addresses mentioned below during working hours: 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 pm (local time) on working days: procurement@ecowas.int with copy to sbangoura@ecowas.int ; bangoura53@yahoo.</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'procurement@ecowas.int', '', 6, 'March 02, 2018');
