(81, 'Consulting', '', '', 'CONSULTANTS VACANCIES AT ECOWAS (more than 100 positions)', '', '<p>Ecowas is recruiting!<br><br><br>The Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) is a regional group of fifteen West African countries. Founded on 28 May 1975, with the signing of the Treaty of Lagos, its mission is to promote economic integration across the region.<br><br>The ECOWAS Commission wishes to update its data base of Consultants as part of the preparation for the implementation of for the years 2018 &amp; 2019.<br><br>The ECOWAS Commission hereby invites reputable qualified consultants (firms or individuals) with vast experience and expertise in the following fields below to apply for the registration exercise:<br><br>1.)&nbsp;Consultant (Industry &amp; Private Sector)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>2.)&nbsp;Consultant (Strategic Planning / Strategic Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>3.)&nbsp;Consultant (Human Resources)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>4.) Consultant (Early Warning and Response)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>5.)&nbsp;Consultant (Legal Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>6.)&nbsp;Consultant (Telecommunications)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>7.) Consultant (Information Technologies (IT))<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br>8.) Consultant (Multilateral Surveillance)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>9.) Consultant (Trade and Customs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>10.) Consultant (Free Movement)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>11.) Consultant (Peace and Security)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>12.) Consultant (Political Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April,<br><br><br>13.)&nbsp;Consultant (Microeconomics Policy)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>14.) Consultant (Monitoring and Evaluation)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>15.)&nbsp;Consultant (Environment Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>16.)&nbsp;Consultant (Mining)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>17.) Consultant (External Relations)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April,<br><br><br>18.)&nbsp;Consultant (Youth &amp; Sports Development)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>19.)&nbsp;Consultant (Health)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>20.) Consultant (Culture and Tourism)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>21.) Consultant (Communications and Journalism)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>22.)&nbsp;Consultant (Quality Management)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>23.) Consultant (Administration)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>24.) Consultant (Education)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>25.) Consultant (Gender)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>26.)&nbsp;Consultant (Humanitarian &amp; Social Affairs)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>27.)&nbsp;Consultant (Infrastructures)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>28.)&nbsp;Consultant (Energy)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>29.)&nbsp;Consultant (Agriculture)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>30.) Consultant (Research &amp; Statistics)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br><br>31.)&nbsp;Consultant (Economics)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br><br>32.)&nbsp;Consultant (Audits)<br><br>Slot: 10<br><br>Deadline: 12th April, 2018.<br><br><br>33.)&nbsp;Individual Consultant (Mid-term Evaluation (MTE) of SIDA&#39;s Support)<br><br>Deadline: 29th March, 2018.<br><br><br><br>34.) Consultant (Recruitment Services)<br><br>Deadline: 26th March, 2018.<br>Method of Application<br>Interested and qualified candidates/firms should send their Expressions of Interest to the address below and clearly marked: &ldquo;Expression of Interest for Registration as Consultant for ECOWAS Commission&rdquo;, Do not open, except in presence of the ECOWAS Procurement Committee:<br>Commissioner General Administration &amp; Conference,<br>ECOWAS Commission,<br>No. 101 Yakubu Gowon Crescent,<br>Asokoro,<br>Abuja.<br><br>Please clearly indicate on the envelope as well as in the covering letter if your submission is for Individual, Consultant or Firm Consultant.<br><br>The Expression of Interest must be submitted in the following order:<br>Cover Letter duly signed by the firm&rsquo;s authorized signatory indicating the area of specialization;<br>Company Profile;<br>Certificate of Incorporation / Registration with the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC);<br>Certified True Copy of Tax Clearance Certificate for the years (2016; 2015 and 2014)<br>Evidence of financial capacity (Certified True Copy of Audited financial statement for the years (2016; 2015 and 2014);<br>CV&rsquo;s of Personnel (copy of all Certificates/Degrees presented)<br>Three (3) verifiable job completion certificate(s) (in the indicated area of interest) executed within the last ten (10) years from 2017;<br>Exact location and full addresses/contact telephone numbers / Email address<br>An Expression of Interest shall be disqualified where any of the above listed documentations is not provided and any job completion certificates submitted by any consultant (firm) must have verifiable and functional address / email and phone number of the client issuing the certificate.<br>Expressions of Interest shall be submitted (1 Original + 3 Copies) in a sealed envelope indicating the name of the consultant (firms or individuals); specific area of specialization.<br>An Expression of Interest shall be disqualified where no specific area of specialization is indicated on the envelope as well as in the cover letter A firm or individual cannot apply for more than three (3) areas of specialization.<br>Note<br>Electronic submissions are not accepted and will therefore not be considered.<br>Interested suppliers / contractors or service providers can obtain further information at the e-mail addresses mentioned below during working hours: 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 pm (local time) on working days: procurement@ecowas.int with copy to sbangoura@ecowas.int ; bangoura53@yahoo.</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'procurement@ecowas.int', '', 6, 'March 02, 2018'),
(82, 'Accounting', '', '', 'A top-notch Stockbroking firm requires the services of a Broker/Research and Treasury/Marketer.', '', '<div dir="auto">EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY IN AN INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT FIRM</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">A top-notch Stockbroking firm requires the services of a Broker/Research and Treasury/Marketer.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><strong><em><u>Job qualifications</u></em></strong></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Stockbroker/Research Analyst</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">1. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must possess a first degree in Business/Social Sciences/Accounting or other related discipline.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">2. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Post graduate qualifications such as MBA, MSC. Economics and the likes will be of added advantage.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">3. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must possess ACS/ICAN/CFA or other professional qualification.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">4. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must be a thorough-bred professional and a person of high integrity.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">5. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must be between the age of 22-35 years.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Treasury Marketer</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">1. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must possess a first degree in Business/Social Sciences/Accounting or other related discipline</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">2. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Post graduate qualifications such as MBA, MSC. Economics and the likes will be of added advantage.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">3. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must possess ACS/ICAN or other professional qualification</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">4. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must have 2 years post NYSC working experience in the Treasury/Investment Banking department of a Bank of other similar financial Institution marketing Money market/Fixed Income or other similar products</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">5. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must be a thorough-bred professional with strong inter-personal skills.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">6. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must have basic knowledge of Treasury operations (TROPS)</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">7. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must be aged between 22-35 years of age</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Please send relevant CV with post being applied for to <a href="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/h/1peyu9o8pao5t/?&cs=wh&v=b&to=job.asset@yahoo.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">job.asset@yahoo.com</a>&nbsp; latest 12th March 2018</div>', 'Nigeria', '', 'job.asset@yahoo.com', '', 10, 'March 05, 2018'),
(83, 'Accounting', '', '', 'vacancy for RELATIONSHIP OFFICER and ASSISTANT ACCOUNTANTS in a manufacturing industry', '', '<div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">One of our clients amongst the leading manufacturing companies requires to fill the followiing positions:</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">1. &nbsp; &nbsp;RELATIONSHIP OFFICERS:</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">* &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Qualification: B.Sc. / HND in Public relation or any &nbsp;related discipline</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">* &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Experience: &nbsp;3 to 4yrs of work experience</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">* &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must be well articulate and command good communication skill</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">* &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Must have good customers&#39; relationship and ability to bring market for &nbsp;the company&#39;s &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; products.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">2. &nbsp; ASSISTANT ACCOUNTANTS:&nbsp;</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Qualification: B.Sc. / HND in accounting or related discipline</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Experience: &nbsp; 4 to 5 years work experience</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ability to use QuickBooks accounting package and Ms Office would be an added &nbsp;advantage.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Knowledge in manufacturing industries is key.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Interested applicants are to forward their CVs to:&nbsp;<a href="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/h/1peyu9o8pao5t/?&cs=wh&v=b&to=kejophconsultingltd@gmail.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">kejophconsultingltd@gmail.com</a> and copy:&nbsp;<a href="https://mail.google.com/mail/u/0/h/1peyu9o8pao5t/?&cs=wh&v=b&to=wallegy4ever@gmail.com" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">wallegy4ever@gmail.com</a> not later than a week from the date of this publication.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Please note: Candidates are advised to use the position applied for as the subject while applying.</div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto"><br></div><div dir="auto">Thank you.&nbsp;</div>', 'Lagos', '', 'kejophconsultingltd@gmail.com', '', 20, 'March 05, 2018'),
(84, 'Hotel', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of Administrative Coordinator at Hilton global Hospitality Company ', '', '<p>Hilton is the leading global hospitality company, spanning the lodging sector from luxurious full-service hotels and resorts to extended-stay suites and mid-priced hotels. For nearly a century, Hilton has offered business and leisure travelers the finest in accommodations, service, amenities and value. Hilton is dedicated to continuing its tradition of providing exceptional guest experiences across its global brands. &nbsp;Our vision to fill the earth with the light and warmth of hospitality unites us as a team to create remarkable hospitality experiences around the world every day. &nbsp;And, our amazing Team Members are at the heart of it all!&nbsp;</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:&nbsp;</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Administrative Coordinator<br></strong></p><p>Job ID: HOT04ZEP</p><p><strong>Location:&nbsp;</strong>Ikeja, Lagos</p><p>Employment Type: Full-time</p><p><strong><br>Job Summary</strong></p><ul><li>An Administrative Coordinator is responsible for carrying out the daily activities of the Executive office to deliver an excellent staff experience while providing secretarial support, managing the mail, and carrying out filing</li><li>Job Role</li></ul><p>As an Administrative Coordinator, you will be responsible for carrying out the daily activities of the Executive office to deliver an excellent staff experience. An Administrative Coordinator will also be required to provide secretarial support, manage mail, and carry out all filing. Specifically, you will be responsible for performing the following tasks to the highest standards:</p><ul><li>Carry out daily administrative activities of the Executive office while adhering to Hilton Standards, policies and procedures</li><li>Provide secretarial support to the Executive team</li><li>Ensure all communications, particularly relating to owners, guests and the Corporate office are handled promptly and professionally</li><li>Receive and distribute mail</li><li>Ensure outgoing mail is dispatched in a timely manner</li><li>Provide minutes to Executive Team Meetings and compile management reports in a timely and accurate manner if necessary</li><li>Maintain adequate supplies of office stationary</li><li>Identify and build internal and external relationships</li><li>Carry out all filing</li><li>Comply with all key security mandates</li><li>Report any maintenance issues or hazards</li><li>Maintain own work area in a clean, tidy and good manner</li><li>Report defective materials and equipment</li><li>Assist with special projects related to the Executive Office</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>What are we looking for?</p><p>An Administrative Coordinator serving Hilton brands is always working on behalf of our Guests and working with other Team Members. To successfully fill this role, you should maintain the attitude, behaviours, skills, and values that follow:</p><ul><li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Excellent administration and IT skills</li><li>Committed to delivering a high level of customer service, both internally and externally</li><li>Flexibility to respond to a range of different work situations</li><li>Ability to work under pressure</li></ul><p>It would be advantageous in this position for you to demonstrate the following capabilities and distinctions:</p><ul><li>Previous administrative experience in a fast paced environment</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>Not Specified.</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="https://jobs.hilton.com/job/Administrative-Coordinator/J3R0M372NV1XZRS00GL" target="_blank"><strong>Click here to apply online</strong></a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 11, 'March 08, 2018'),
(85, 'IT and Communication', '', '', 'Apply as Application Developer at the Nigerian stock exchange', '', '<p>The Nigerian Stock Exchange, services the largest economy in Africa, and is championing the development of Africa&#39;s financial markets. The Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing services, market data solutions, ancillary technology services, and more. It is an open, professional and vibrant exchange, connecting Nigeria, Africa and the world.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Application Developer<br><br>Location</strong>: Lagos</p><p>Division: Trading Business Division&nbsp;</p><p>Department: Market Services Department</p><p>Role: Application Developer&nbsp;</p><p>Report to: Head-Market Services&nbsp;</p><p>Grade: Application Developer</p><p>Estimated Date Of Resumption: Monday, April 2, 2018</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><ul><li>The Nigerian Stock Exchange services the largest economy in Africa, and is championing the development of Africa&rsquo;s financial markets.</li><li>The Exchange offers listing and trading services, licensing services, market data solutions, ancillary technology services, and more.</li><li>The Nigerian Stock Exchange continues to evolve to meet the needs of its valued customers, and to achieve the highest level of competitiveness.</li><li>It is an open, professional and vibrant exchange, connecting Nigeria, Africa and the world.</li><li>The Application Developer role is a technology focused role intended to provide software development and analysis services to the NSE.</li><li>The role sits within the Trading Business division and under the Market Services Department specifically.</li><li>The role would suit someone with proven experience building production, commercial-quality web based applications (in C# 3.0 and above) that also has proven in depth SQL-Server development experience.</li><li>Applicants must be comfortable with advanced SQL syntax, SQL Server Business Intelligence development and SQL Server (additional experience with Oracle is highly desirable).</li><li>The incumbent needs to be flexible and open to new ideas or change with the passion and drive to excel in their career.</li><li>S/he must recognize the value of agile, iterative development processes, SDLC and have strong OOD and OOA skills.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>The Application Developer will be expected to have aptitudes, skills, knowledge and experience on the following areas:</p><ul><li>Demonstrable analytical skills with regard to specifying and detailing business processes and requirements</li><li>Delivery experience with .NET framework, including C#, ADO.NET, LINQ and ASP.NET</li><li>Extensive experience with SQL Server (2008/2012)</li><li>Experience with SQL data business intelligence (OLAP, etc.) preferred</li><li>Advanced knowledge and experience in HTML and DHTML, JavaScript, CSS</li><li>Practical experience in Agile development methodologies</li><li>Ability to work both in a collaborative team environment and independently</li><li>Proficient verbal and written communication skills</li><li>Experience with implementation and testing of DB backups, restores and recovery models</li><li>Database server deployment design, processes, and day-to-day operations, including monitoring and Performance Tuning and Optimization (PTO) using native monitoring and troubleshooting tools</li><li>Formulation, management and execution of data test strategies, plans and delivery commitments in concert with business and project management efforts</li><li>Mobile and web service development experience</li><li>Experience with ticketing systems (e.g.; JIRA, Bugzilla) and managed workflows</li><li>Experience with SharePoint 2010 and above preferred</li><li>Strong familiarity with source control systems (e.g. Team Foundation Server)</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications and Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s Degree (B.S./B.A.), Computer Science or similar</li><li>Minimum 5 years of application and web application development experience (using the .Net Framework 3.0 and above). Other fields of study are acceptable when combined with strong background or work experience within the financial sector.</li></ul><p>Functional Competencies:</p><ul><li>Analytical Thinking</li><li>Concept Development and Execution Management</li><li>Database Administration</li><li>Enterprise Architecture</li><li>Information Management</li><li>Network Planning and Design</li><li>Software Engineering and Development</li><li>System Analysis and Design</li></ul><p>Behavioural Competencies:</p><ul><li>Attention to Detail</li><li>Change Management</li><li>Effective Communication Skills (Written &amp; Oral)</li><li>Innovation</li><li>Leadership</li><li>Problem Solving</li><li>Result Oriented</li><li>Time Management</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>9th March, 2018.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="https://www.nse.com.ng:8443/careers/#/vacancy/57" target="_blank"><strong>Click here to apply online</strong></a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 7, 'March 08, 2018'),
(86, 'Lecturing', '', '', 'More than 58 Positions at AFE Babalola University', '', '<p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><a href="http://www.hotnigerianjobs.com/company/afe-babalola-university-ado-ekiti/">Afe Babalola University, Ado-Ekiti (ABUAD)</a>, a Federal Government-licensed, Non Profit Private University is a model which is unique in many ways. In founding the university, the purpose and objective of the Founder is to reform education in Nigeria by providing and leading others in quality education, service, industry and character as well as discipline.&nbsp;</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>Applications are invited from suitably qualified and experienced candidates for the under- listed academic position in the discipline below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Lecturer II<br><br>Location:&nbsp;</strong>Ekiti State</p><p>College: Social and Management Sciences</p><p>Discipline: Media and Communication Studies</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Candidates must possess Ph.D. degree in Mass Communication/Media and Communication Studies or related qualification with specialization in Print Media from a recognized University within or outside Nigeria Or candidates must possess Ph.D. degree in Mass Communication/Media and Communication or any related qualification with specialization in Public Relations and Advertising (PRAD) and News Media from a recognized University within or outside Nigeria.</li><li>Must have substantial scholarly publications in reputable journals</li><li>Candidates must possess teaching and research experience in the University</li><li>Appointment for this position would be determined by the number of years of teaching experience and publications</li></ul><p><strong>Remuneration</strong></p><p>Salary and other conditions of service are to what obtain in the Nigerian University System.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>27th March, 2018.</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should send their Applications to the address below:</p><p><strong>Afe Babalola University,<br>KM 8.5, Afe Babalola University Way,<br>Ado-Ekiti (Directly Opposite the Federal Polytechnic)<br>Ado-Ekiti,<br>Ekitit State.<br></strong>Or<strong><br></strong>Email:<strong>&nbsp;</strong><a href="mailto:academicjobs@abuad.edu.ng" target="_blank"><strong>academicjobs@abuad.edu.ng</strong></a></p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>Applicants are advised to request their Referees to send their reports under confidential cover to the address above.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Note:</strong> Only shortlisted candidates will be invited for the interview.</p>', 'Ekiti', '', 'academicjobs@abuad.edu.ng', '', 26, 'March 08, 2018'),
(87, 'Research', '', '', 'Vacancy for Senior M & E Officer at Malaria Consortium', '', '<p><br>Malaria Consortium is one of the world&rsquo;s leading non-profit organisations specialising in the comprehensive prevention, control and treatment of malaria and other communicable diseases among vulnerable and under privileged populations. We increasingly find our work on malaria can be effectively integrated with other similar public health interventions for greater impact and therefore expanded our remit to include child health and neglected tropical disease interventions.<br>Job Title: Senior M&amp;E Officer<br><br>Locations: Gombe, Jigawa, Kaduna, Kebbi and Yobe<br><br>Department: Technical<br><br>Length of Contract: 3 years<br><br>Hours: 40<br><br>Reporting to: Line manager: Zonal Project Manager/State Technical Officer<br><br>Grade: 8<br><br>Job Purpose<br><br>The Senior M&amp;E Officer will serve as the main focal person for all Research, MEAL (Monitoring, Evaluation, Accountability and Learning) activity which includes data validation, DQA, coordination meetings, capacity building in data quality and supportive supervisory visit to strengthen health management information system in Global Fund project in the state<br>S/he will assist and report to the state project manager / State technical officer regarding the monitoring and evaluation of project activities.<br>Scope of Work<br><br>The incumbent will work as part of the project team under the direct supervision and guidance of the state Project Manager (Kano, Niger and Yobe states) / state technical officer 3 Last updated 20/02/2018<br>(Gombe, Kaduna and Jigawa) and indirectly through the Country Technical Coordinator (CTC) for the attainment of the project goal.<br>Key Working Relationships<br><br>The officer working under the line-management of the State Coordinator and in close collaboration with the state, LGA, community actors, stakeholders and partners would deliver aspects of the project as per the specified job tasks and expected deliverables.<br>Key Accountabilities<br>Technical Contributions (50%):<br><br>Plan and implement M&amp;E activities in the approved work plan under the guidance of the Zone Project Manager/ state coordinator<br>Based on the MEAL plan for the project, develop, review, and ensured correct implementation of the Global Fund Malaria MEAL state MEAL Implementation Plan and procedures<br>Lead the set up and maintenance of a project database and linkages with the national DHIS version 2 platform for reporting<br>Ensure availability of high quality routine data for all malaria indicators / parameters (both case management and prevention) and other project related data from all levels of health facilities (3o, 2o, 1o)<br>In Niger and Kebbi, to also ensure high quality data are available in useable format on a regular and timely basis for programmatic decision making by facilitating data collection and entry from:<br>CORP&rsquo;s service utilization register<br>CORP&rsquo;s status update form to capture changes to the CORP&rsquo;s status in relation to the project (e.g. withdrawal, change of supervisor, lost to follow ups, etc.)<br>Supervision checklist to capture the details of the supervision visits<br>Demand creation activity recording form to capture activities carried out by the demand creation team<br>A logistics form that captures the logistic component of the project, including drug distributions, and other related equipment and tools<br>Plan regular data quality assessments, and ensure the completeness, consistency and validity of routine data<br>Work with the M&amp;E Manager on timely submission of high quality programmatic Progress Update and Disbursement Request (PUDR) and the validation of such on a quarterly basis according to the approved project performance framework<br>Work with project team to facilitate the documentation of activities in form of reports and ensure proper archiving of such for easy access and reference<br>Plan and coordinate quarterly routine monitoring visits to project supported sites and provide supportive supervision<br>Provide direct technical assistance and capacity building for state and LGA level implementers in the design and implementation of GF- supported monitoring and evaluation activities<br>Participate in project assessments, evaluations and design including development of survey protocols with support from country office and advisors<br>Perform other duties as assigned.<br>Program Management (10%):<br><br>Support SMoH staff with coordinating program management activities, by ensuring that the recommended coordination meetings hold at the LGA and state levels<br>Work with the state and LGA Ministry of Health staff to ensure that reports are obtained from all health facilities within the state through appropriate state-specific mechanisms<br>Participate in regular monitoring and supervisory visits to the GF-supported health facilities, and ensure that action plans are developed for identified gaps<br>Support health facilities with ensuring that all items in the action plans are addressed and all outstanding gaps are closed<br>Accountability (10%):<br><br>Support programming staff to engage key populations in monitoring and evaluating program&rsquo;s performance and to incorporate participatory methods into M&amp;E systems in Nigeria<br>Orient program staff and partners on the basic principles and practices of beneficiary accountability in Nigeria<br>Support the development and implementation of feedback and response channels to reflect the preferences of community members and beneficiaries<br>Ensure that beneficiary feedback is adequately documented, addressed, analysed, and utilized by program teams<br>Knowledge Management and Learning (20%):<br><br>Ensure that state M&amp;E and program teams regularly review and accordingly adjust M&amp;E plans and tools in the light of changes and needs in the field context based on monitoring data and reflection sessions<br>Support learning-to-action events and reflection sessions to systematically analyze data for programmatic use for the state, and to document and incorporate lessons learned into program design and implementation<br>Conduct regular data review and analysis for feedback to states for program improvement, and for updates to national level (MC and government)<br>Support program staff in key activities including development of a learning agenda, organizing regular learning events, supporting operations research, and reflecting, documentation, and communication of learning initiatives<br>Support knowledge management systems and practices to gather, document and share best practices with project team, MC country office, government and technical partners. Collaborate with M&amp;E and program staff to develop learning briefs, project bulletins and other materials for dissemination.<br>Promote adoption of the best practices in knowledge management by other project staff and government partners<br>Representation (10%):<br><br>Liaise with technical counterparts in the State Ministry of Health, PRs, SRs, and other local stakeholders engaged in malaria activities in Nigeria<br>Participate in events/ meetingsrelated to Monitoring, Evaluation and research, including quarterly Principal Recipient and Sub-recipients quarterly review meetings<br>Actively participate in the M&amp;E Community of Practice with other PR, SRs and government M&amp;E staff<br>JOB REQUIREMENTS<br>MIN REQUIRED EXPERIENCE:<br><br>3 year(s)<br>MIN QUALIFICATION:<br><br>Bachelor&#39;s Degree/HND<br>DESIRED COURSES:<br><br>Not Specified<br>OTHER REQUIREMENTS:<br><br>Qualifications and Experience:<br>Essential:<br>Degree in Statistics, Demography, Mathematics or any other relevant quantitative discipline<br>Demonstrable contextual knowledge of local issues, community priorities, social and cultural constraints and realities related to community assessment, project design, evaluation and implementation<br>Cognate experience in monitoring and evaluation of community-based interventions is highly desirable<br>Experience in managing HMIS and CLMS as well as familiarity with Nigerian public sector health systems and Global Fund programme implementation will be added advantages.<br>Experience in survey design and implementation, development of data bases and analysis and write up of survey results<br>Demonstrated skills in data management and quantitative data analysis<br><br>Desirable:<br><br>At least 3 years&rsquo; experience attending quarterly Principal Recipient and Sub-recipients quarterly review meetings<br>Fluency in written and spoken English<br>Work-based Skills and Competencies<br>Essential:<br><br>A solid understanding of health systems strengthening<br>Proficiency in database management especially DHIS; Excel, Word, PowerPoint and demonstrable experience with statistical software packages (Stata, SPSS, Epi Info)<br>Strong analytical skills and experience interpreting a strategic vision into an operational model<br>Proven writing, communication and presentation skills in English<br>A collaborative and flexible style, with a strong service mentality<br>Facilitation and coordination skills<br>The ideal candidate must be attentive to detail, highly organised, flexible and self-motivated with excellent communication skills in written and oral communication<br>He/she must clearly display the ability to effectively prioritise and perform tasks to meet tight deadlines<br>Desirable:<br><br>Skills in qualitative research<br>Core Competencies<br>Delivering Results:<br>Level C - Supports others to achieve results:<br><br>Displays a positive and enthusiastic approach and is not deterred by setbacks, finding alternative ways to reach goals or targets<br>Supports others to plan and deliver results<br>Supports others to manage and cope with setbacks<br>Analysis and Use of Information:<br>Level C - Works confidently with complex data to support work:<br><br>Interprets complex written information<br>Works confidently with data before making decisions, for example; interpreting trends, issues and risks<br>Acquainted with the validity, relevance and limitations of different sources of evidence<br>Interpersonal and Communications:<br><br>Level C - Adapts communications effectively<br>Tailors communication (content, style and medium) to diverse audiences<br>Communicates equally effectively at all organisational levels<br>Understands others&rsquo; underlying needs, concerns and motivations and communicates effectively in sensitive situations<br>Resolves intra-team and inter-team conflicts effectively<br>Collaboration and Partnering:<br>Level B - Collaborates effectively across teams:<br><br>Proactive in providing and seeking support from expert colleagues<br>Raises difficult issues with teams/ partners and stakeholders with a view to positive resolution<br>Proactive in building a rapport with a diverse range of people<br>Leading and Motivating People:<br><br>Level B - Manages own development and seeks opportunities:<br>Manages own development and performance positively<br>Learns lessons from successes and failures<br>Seeks and explores opportunities within Malaria Consortium which develop skills and expertise.<br>Salary/Benefits<br>4,189,500<br><br>Application Closing Date<br>21st March, 2018.<br><br>Method of Application<br>Interested and qualified candidates should:<br>Use link to apply online<br><br>Visit link For More Information (PDF)<br>http://www.malariaconsortium.org/HRDocuments/JDSeniorMonitoring&amp;EvaluationOfficerGF.pdf</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 14, 'March 10, 2018'),
(88, 'Select Post Category', '', '', 'Vacancy for Finance Manager at a leading luxurious kitchen fittings outfit, Lagos Island axis of ', '', '<p>A leading luxurious kitchen fittings outfit located on the Island axis of Lagos, is looking to recruit a Finance Manager.<br><br>Reporting line: Managing Director<br><br>Job location: Lagos Mainland<br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>Job Functions:<br><br>Funds Management:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ensure that sufficient funds are available to meet ongoing operational requirements.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Assist in determining the company&#39;s proper capital structure.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Forecast, monitor and interpret cash flows and plan for future cash needs.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Develop financial management mechanisms that minimize financial risk, overall cost reduction and cost control.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Conduct reviews and evaluations for cost-reduction opportunities.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage the company&#39;s financial accounting, monitoring and reporting systems.<br><br>Budgeting:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Manage the preparation of the company&#39;s budget.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Report to management on variances from the established budget, and the reasons for those variances.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Assist management in the formulation of its overall strategic direction.<br><br>Financial Analysis:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Engage in ongoing cost reduction analyses in all areas of the company.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Engage in benchmarking studies to establish areas of potential operational improvement.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Interpret the company&#39;s financial results to management and recommend improvement activities.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Liaise with auditors to ensure annual monitoring is carried out.<br><br>Inventory Management/Operations:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Monitor the day-to-day financial operations within the company, such as payroll, invoicing, and other transactions.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Seek out methods for minimizing financial risk to the company.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Review financial data and prepare monthly and annual reports.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Develop external relationships with appropriate contacts, e.g. auditors, and statutory organizations. Etc.<br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>Technical Skills:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Inventory Management Experience<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Accounts Payable<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Accounts Receivable<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Personal Attributes:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Articulate and organized<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Possesses strong Entrepreneurial mindset<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Smart and Energetic<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Ability to communicate effectively<br>&nbsp;<br>Required Qualification/Experience:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Minimum of a first degree (BSC/HND) in Accounting.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Professional certification (ICAN/ACCA) will be an added advantage.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Minimum of 3 years&rsquo; experience in similar role<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Pay: 180-200k<br>&nbsp;<br>Interested and qualified candidates should send their cvs to careers@kennediaconsulting.net , using &ldquo;Finance Manager&rdquo; as subject of mail.<br>&nbsp;<br>Deadline: Thursday, March 15 2018.</p>', 'Select Post Location', '', '', '', 7, 'March 14, 2018'),
(89, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Vacancy for Finance Manager at a leading luxurious kitchen fittings outfit, Lagos Island ', '', '<p>A leading luxurious kitchen fittings outfit located on the Island axis of Lagos, is looking to recruit a Finance Manager.<br><br><br>Job location: Lagos Mainland<br><br>&nbsp;<br><br><strong><em>Job Role</em></strong><br><br>Funds Management:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; Ensure that sufficient funds are available to meet ongoing operational requirements.<br>&middot; &nbsp;Assist in determining the company&#39;s proper capital structure.<br>&middot; &nbsp; Forecast, monitor and interpret cash flows and plan for future cash needs.<br>&middot;<span style="background-color: transparent;">&nbsp;Develop financial management mechanisms that minimize financial risk, overall cost reduction and cost control.</span></p><p>&middot; &nbsp;Conduct reviews and evaluations for cost-reduction opportunities.<br>&middot; &nbsp;Manage the company&#39;s financial accounting, monitoring and reporting systems.<br><br>Budgeting:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp;Manage the preparation of the company&#39;s budget.<br><br>&middot; Report to management on variances from the established budget, and the reasons for those variances.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; Assist management in the formulation of its overall strategic direction.<br><br>Financial Analysis:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; Engage in ongoing cost reduction analyses in all areas of the company.<br><br>&middot; &nbsp;Engage in benchmarking studies to establish areas of potential operational improvement.<br><br>&middot; Interpret the company&#39;s financial results to management and recommend improvement activities.<br><br>&middot; Liaise with auditors to ensure annual monitoring is carried out.<br><br>Inventory Management/Operations:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp;Monitor the day-to-day financial operations within the company, such as payroll, invoicing, and other transactions.<br>&middot; Seek out methods for minimizing financial risk to the company.<br>&middot; Review financial data and prepare monthly and annual reports.<br>&middot; Develop external relationships with appropriate contacts, e.g. auditors, and statutory organizations. Etc.<br><br>&nbsp;<br><br>Technical Skills:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp;Inventory Management Experience<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; Accounts Payable<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; Accounts Receivable<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Personal Attributes:<br><br>&middot; &nbsp;Articulate and organized<br>&middot; &nbsp; Possesses strong Entrepreneurial mindset<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp;Smart and Energetic<br>&middot; &nbsp; Ability to communicate effectively<br>&nbsp;<br><strong><em>Required Qualification/Experience:</em></strong><br><br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp; Minimum of a first degree (BSC/HND) in Accounting.<br>&middot; &nbsp; &nbsp;Professional certification (ICAN/ACCA) will be an added advantage.<br>&middot; &nbsp; Minimum of 3 years&rsquo; experience in similar role<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Pay: 180-200k<br>&nbsp;<br>Interested and qualified candidates should send their cvs to careers@kennediaconsulting.net , using &ldquo;Finance Manager&rdquo; as subject of mail.<br><strong>&nbsp;<br>Deadline: Thursday, March 15 2018.</strong></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'careers@kennediaconsulting.net', '', 14, 'March 14, 2018'),
(90, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Vacancy for Experienced accountant at Reliabuild, Abuja', '', '<p><strong>dr</strong>Reliabuild is in need of an Accountant in Abuja&nbsp;</p><p>Qualifications</p><p>Knowledge of general accepted accounting theories, principles, methods, practices and terminology.&nbsp;</p><p>Minimum of 3 years work exp. ICAN or equivalent will be an added advantage.</p><p>How to Apply</p><p>&nbsp;Send CV&#39;s/Resumes to: contact@reliabuild.com.ng</p>', 'Abuja', '', 'contact@reliabuild.com.ng', '', 13, 'March 15, 2018'),
(91, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Vacancy for  Sales/Customer Service Officers', '', '<p>Our client is one of the largest car buying service in Nigeria with the goal of helping hundreds of customers to sell their cars with lots of inspection centres at strategic locations to make it easy for our dear customers to sell their cars.<br>We are currently recruiting &ldquo;sales/customer service officers&rdquo; for our client for various locations in Lagos.<br><br>ROLE &ndash; Sales/Customer Service Officers<br>LOCATION - Lagos<br><br>REQUIREMENTS<br>&bull; &nbsp;Minimum of B.Sc/HND in any course.<br>&bull; &nbsp;Qualified candidates must have solid experience in a customer relationship management role.<br>&bull; &nbsp;Must have Excellent Communication skills, organisational skills, administrative and negotiation skills<br>&bull; &nbsp;Proficient in Microsoft Office and Basic Computer Skills<br>&bull; &nbsp;Very presentable, good dress sense and self-confident.<br><br>HOW TO APPLY<br>Qualified persons should apply by sending an updated copy of their CV to resume@rovedana.com. The subject of the mail should be &ldquo;Sales/Customer Service Officer&rdquo;</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'resume@rovedana.com.', '', 8, 'March 15, 2018'),
(92, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Vacancy for  Sales/Customer Service Officers', '', '<p>Our client is one of the largest car buying service in Nigeria with the goal of helping hundreds of customers to sell their cars with lots of inspection centres at strategic locations to make it easy for our dear customers to sell their cars.<br>We are currently recruiting &ldquo;sales/customer service officers&rdquo; for our client for various locations in Lagos.<br><br>ROLE &ndash; Sales/Customer Service Officers<br>LOCATION - Lagos<br><br>REQUIREMENTS<br>&bull; &nbsp;Minimum of B.Sc/HND in any course.<br>&bull; &nbsp;Qualified candidates must have solid experience in a customer relationship management role.<br>&bull; &nbsp;Must have Excellent Communication skills, organisational skills, administrative and negotiation skills<br>&bull; &nbsp;Proficient in Microsoft Office and Basic Computer Skills<br>&bull; &nbsp;Very presentable, good dress sense and self-confident.<br><br>HOW TO APPLY<br>Qualified persons should apply by sending an updated copy of their CV to resume@rovedana.com. The subject of the mail should be &ldquo;Sales/Customer Service Officer&rdquo;</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'resume@rovedana.com', '', 19, 'March 15, 2018'),
(93, 'Agriculture/Farming', '', '', 'FRESH: VACANCY FOR WORKERS AT CASHEW PROCESSING PLANT, ILORIN', '', '<p>A fast growing CASHEW PROCESSING PLANT located at GRA, ILORIN is urgently recruiting workers.</p><p><strong><em>Job specification</em></strong></p><p>Female Applicants should apply immediately</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong><em>How to apply</em></strong></p><p><em>Apply in person or call Adetutu ADEBISI &nbsp;on</em></p><p><em>08060667403</em></p><p><br></p>', 'Ilorin ', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 47, 'March 20, 2018'),
(94, 'Internship', '', '', 'Vacancy for IT STUDENTS (Engineering)', '', '<p>A mechanical engineering student is needed for 1yr I.T and one electrical engineering for NYSC (corper).<br>Not later than 2:00pm tomorrow, to &nbsp;work in a construction company on the island.</p><p>How to apply</p><p>Call<br>07061937283 or send CV to<br>Emmanueljustice92@gmail.com</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 11, 'March 22, 2018');
INSERT INTO `jobs` (`id`, `job_cate`, `name`, `email`, `job_title`, `demo`, `job_des`, `job_loc`, `job_deadline`, `job_contact`, `ext_link`, `hit`, `date`) VALUES
(95, 'Technician', '', '', 'Vacancy for Geographic Information Systems Officers@Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC', '', '<p>Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC) - Buoyed by a mission to redefine customer experience and be the provider of choice wherever energy is consumed, Ikeja Electricity Distribution Plc (Ikeja Electric), Nigeria&#39;s largest power distribution network powers lives and businesses with innovation and unwavering drive for excellence. The company began its new phase of growth and expansion on November 1st, 2013 following the handover of the defunct Power Holding Company of Nigeria (PHCN) to NEDC/ KEPCO Consortium under the privatization scheme of the Federal Government of Nigeria.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Geographic Information Systems Officers<br></strong></p><p>Job Type: Full time</p><p>Reporting To: Geographic Information Systems Coordinator</p><p><strong><br>Role Purpose</strong></p><ul><li>Asset mapping, data creation, management, and analysis to support comprehensive planning processes and activities within Ikeja Electric</li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Designing, implementing, customizing and maintaining Utility (electricity) specific GIS.&nbsp;</li><li>Providing quality control with regard to discipline specific in-house data capture (data conversion), the evaluation of data acquired from the field and network database construction.</li><li>Developing, maintaining and updating the Business Unit GIS databases for planning, monitoring and decision making purposes.</li><li>Manipulating GIS data to create information products to meet electricity distribution and marketing needs.&nbsp;</li><li>Developing and applying GIS analysis solutions to meet the overall business needs.&nbsp;</li><li>Serving as the GIS technical lead and point of contact on GIS and related matters at the BU level.</li><li>Capture GIS data in different formats using GPS, electronic data recorders, digitizers, and other means.</li><li>Download, convert and upload GIS data available from internal and external sources to make them user-friendly.</li><li>Catalog and inventory GIS data, including metadata creation.</li><li>Input, update and maintain GIS databases, including backups and also maintaining linkages to other databases.</li><li>Perform GIS spatial analyses.</li><li>Capture and update network data as regards new or previously uncaptured customers, network components and so on.</li><li>Create map layouts and views, and generate maps and reports.</li><li>Develop new applications and train others in the use of these applications.</li><li>Comply with Quality Management System / Occupational Health &amp; Safety requirements including objectives and applicable regulations relating to assigned jobs</li><li>Assist in Carry out any other duties as requested by the Head of Department</li></ul><p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>B.Sc in Geography, Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, Geology, Surveying, Urban Planning and Geographic Information Systems</li><li>General knowledge of IT skills, including the use and manipulation of SQL databases and spreadsheets, and knowledge of specialized software packages such as ESRI ArcGIS or QGIS</li></ul><p>Technical Competencies:</p><ul><li>Network Location Mapping</li><li>Network Data Analysis Management</li><li>Electricity Industry Regulatory Knowledge</li><li>Customer Information Management</li><li>View/Query/Analysis</li><li>Spatial Network Data Management</li></ul><p>Behavioral Competencies:</p><ul><li>Communication and Interpersonal Relations</li><li>Supervisory/Managerial Skills</li><li>Problem Solving and Decision Making</li><li>Managing Resources</li><li>Business Focus</li><li>Presentation Skills</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>28th March, 2018.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="http://careers.ikejaelectric.com/position/view/48" target="_blank"><strong>Click here to apply online</strong></a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 9, 'March 23, 2018'),
(96, 'Technician', '', '', 'Vacancy for Geographic InfVacancy for Analyst@Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC', '', '<p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC) - Buoyed by a mission to redefine customer experience and be the provider of choice wherever energy is consumed, Ikeja Electricity Distribution Plc (Ikeja Electric), Nigeria&#39;s largest power distribution network powers lives and businesses with innovation and unwavering drive for excellence. The company began its new phase of growth and expansion on November 1st, 2013 following the handover of the defunct Power Holding Company of Nigeria (PHCN) to NEDC/ KEPCO Consortium under the privatization scheme of the Federal Government of Nigeria.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Analyst<br><br>Location:&nbsp;</strong>Lagos</p><p>Job Title: Full time</p><p>Reporting To: Head Vigilance Strategy, Monitoring &amp; Loss Reduction</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Role Purpose</strong></p><ul><li>Monitor Business Unit / Undertaking Performance, providing support in the areas of analytics and reporting.</li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate Monthly performance review by the various Undertakings within the Business Unit</li><li>Collate and interpret data, analyzing results from varied sources such as Fault Log/ Register, Transformer Lost in Circuit, Hourly Load Readings, Feeder Availability, Customer Complaints Log, Energy Delivered etc, from the Business Units / Undertakings using statistical techniques and providing ongoing reports, drawing inference and presenting observations to the business to ensure operational efficiency</li><li>Monitor BU performance relative to set targets</li><li>Regularly update the &nbsp;performance dashboard for the Business Unit and Undertakings cascaded from the Head Office</li><li>Identifying, analyzing, and interpreting collection/ billing efficiency, customer delinquency trends or patterns based on past or historical performance of the business unit/ undertaking.</li><li>Generates commercial/ technical periodic reports (daily, weekly and monthly) such as collection analysis reports, energy availability reports, sub-station maintenance reports etc as may be required by the management team.</li><li>Track and report the Business Unit/ Undertaking KPIs such on a monthly basis</li><li>Ensure compliance to reporting standards by the Undertakings/ Business Unit as required by the Corporate Performance Monitoring Team within the Head Office.</li><li>Handles adhoc reporting duties as may be required from time to time by the Business Unit</li><li>Establish and maintain relationships with key stakeholders</li><li>Provide general support to the Business Managers as may be required</li><li>Perform any other duty as may be communicated by Corporate Performance Lead or BU Management Team</li></ul><p><strong>Minimum Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor&#39;s degree in any of the following disciplines &ndash; Engineering, Accounting, Economics, Banking &amp; Finance or other numerate discipline</li><li>2-3 years relevant work experience, from related sector/ organization with demonstrable understanding of data analytics.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Microsoft Office suite: Word, Excel and PowerPoint.</li></ul><p>Technical Competencies:</p><ul><li>Basic knowledge of the power industry and the distribution value chain</li><li>Strategic management</li><li>Data Analytics</li></ul><p>Behavioral Competencies:</p><ul><li>Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy</li><li>Strong problem solving skills</li><li>Excellent interpersonal negotiation and communications skills</li><li>Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings.</li><li>Good Team player</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>30th March, 2018.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should:</p><p><a href="http://careers.ikejaelectric.com/position/view/47" target="_blank"><strong>Click here to apply online</strong></a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 16, 'March 23, 2018'),
(97, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for Compliance Officer at Equity Assurance Plc.', '', '<p><br>Equity Assurance Plc. was recently acquired by SUNU Group (a leading PAN-African Insurance Group) with presence in 16 countries across twenty three locations in Francophone, Central and West African markets. Equity Assurance Plc. is duly licensed by the National Insurance Commission to underwrite all classes of general business.<br><br>We are recruiting to fill the vacant position below:<br><br>Job Title: Compliance Officer (Legal)<br><br>Location: Lagos, Nigeria.<br><br><strong><em>Key Duties</em></strong><br>Coordinates with the HLC regarding the planning, risk assessment and reviews needed for the annual compliance report in order to comply with industry compliance reports.<br>Assists with Compliance as it relates to Sub-advised relationships and due-diligence reviews.<br>Responds and provides guidance to daily compliance inquiries from subsidiaries and other senior professionals in the group<br>Assists with the company&#39;s Anti-Money Laundering (&quot;AML&quot;) and Sanctions Programs,<br>Supports AML compliance training within the group<br>Assists in coordinating the group&#39;s responses to regulatory examination by regulatory bodies<br>Liaises with counterparts in the branches and foreign offices on compliance issues.<br>Assists with vendor and sub-advisor due diligence<br>Assists with documentary portfolio guidelines and monitoring thereof<br>Prepare recommendations and reports for HLC / management</p><p><br></p><p><br><strong>Qualification</strong><br>Bachelor in Law , LLB Hons<br>Experience:<br>3 - 5 years&rsquo; working experience<br>Experience in Insurance will be an added advantage.<br>Professional Certification:<br>Membership of the Nigerian Bar Association<br>The Person must have:<br>Understanding of judicial process<br>Good Understanding of Nigerian Law<br>Proficient in the use of Microsoft Office Suite<br>Abreast with Industry &amp; Regulatory changes<br><br>Application Closing Date<br>Not Specified.<br><br>How to apply:<br>interested and qualified candidates should send their CV to hrteam@equityassuranceplc.com</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'hrteam@equityassuranceplc.com', '', 23, 'March 26, 2018'),
(98, 'IT and Communication', '', '', 'Contract Jobs _ Web designer, Graphic Designer, Online CONTENT,Copywriter AND SCRIPT WRITER ', '', '<p><br><br>WEB DESIGNER<br><br>A part&nbsp;TIME web designer needed on a contract basis.</p><p>&nbsp;With the mandate to design 5 Professional website every 2 weeks. You only need to report once a week except You need to come in to use office facility to execute your job. You are only paid per for job done excellently and you are require to do all corrections on the job till customer is satisfied .<br><br><br>Skill; Programming&nbsp;skills, WordPress,&nbsp;Joomla ,&nbsp;PHP,&nbsp;java&nbsp;etc.<br><br>Fee: 30,000 every 2 weeks of 5 sites delivered.<br><br><br>You will be required to submit 2&nbsp;guarantors .&nbsp;Must have all equipment required to get your jobs done.<br><br>This is a 24 hour immediate resumption Job.<br><br><br>Applicant should send CV to&nbsp;Hr@gtextgroup.com.ng&nbsp;and copyme@stephenakintayo.com<br><br><br>Interviews&nbsp;Holds&nbsp;Gtext Hub, 3rd Floor 51/52 Ijaye Road, Ogba Bus Stop, Lagos.<br>Wednesday 28th March&nbsp;by&nbsp;12noon.<br>( no rescheduling&nbsp;allowed ,&nbsp;only apply if you can be available that date and can resume next day if selected).<br><br><br>2)GRAPHIC DESIGNER<br><br>A Part TIME Graphics needed on a contract basis. With the mandate to design 30 New Designs weekly and 30 similar designs. You only need to report once a week except You need to come in to use office facility to execute your job. You are only paid per for job done excellently and you&nbsp;are require&nbsp;to do all corrections on the job assign till&nbsp;customer&nbsp;is&nbsp;satisfied .<br><br><br>Must be&nbsp;skillfull&nbsp;in Photoshop and very creative with unconventional designs.<br><br>30,000 for every two weeks of target design being Completed.<br><br><br>You will be required to submit 2&nbsp;guarantors .&nbsp;Must have all equipment required to get your jobs done.<br><br>This is a 24 hour immediate resumption Job.<br><br>Applicant should send CV to&nbsp;Hr@gtextgroup.com.ng&nbsp;and copyme@stephenakintayo.com<br><br><br>Interviews&nbsp;Holds&nbsp;Gtext Hub, 3rd Floor 51/52 Ijaye Road, Ogba Bus Stop, Lagos.<br>Wednesday&nbsp;28th March&nbsp;by&nbsp;12 noon.<br>( no rescheduling&nbsp;allowed ,&nbsp;only apply if you can be available that date and can resume next day if selected).<br><br><br>3) Online CONTENT,Copywriter&nbsp;AND&nbsp;SCRIPT WRITER<br>A Part TIME content writer,&nbsp;copy writer&nbsp;and&nbsp;script writer&nbsp;needed on a contract basis.<br>With the mandate to write&nbsp;30&nbsp;New Content 200 words content every week edit 30&nbsp;write ups&nbsp;and prepare website content for 3 websites WEEKLY. You only need to report once a week except You need to come in to use office facility to execute your job. You are only paid per for job done excellently and you&nbsp;are require&nbsp;to do all corrections on the job assign till&nbsp;customer&nbsp;is&nbsp;satisfied .<br><br><br>You will be required to submit 2&nbsp;guarantors .&nbsp;Must have all equipment required to get your jobs done.<br>25,000 WEEKLY for target contents written&nbsp;and&nbsp;edited .<br><br>This is a 24 hour immediate resumption Job.<br><br>Applicant should send CV to&nbsp;Hr@gtextgroup.com.ng&nbsp;and copyme@stephenakintayo.com<br><br><br>Interviews&nbsp;Holds&nbsp;Gtext Hub, 3rd Floor 51/52 Ijaye Road, Ogba Bus Stop, Lagos.<br>Wednesday&nbsp;28th March&nbsp;by&nbsp;12 noon.<br>( no rescheduling allowed , only apply if you can be available that date and can resume next day if selected</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'copyme@stephenakintayo.com', '', 27, 'March 27, 2018'),
(100, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for Client services officer at Home and you Ltd', '', '<p>&nbsp;Home and you is an Interior Design Firm a full blown furniture designers and manufacturers<br>Job description.<br>Maintain high level of professionalism and competence in every client interaction.<br>Build positive and productive relationships with clients.<br>Make frequent client calls and visits atimes to strengthen client relationships.<br>Analyze and resolve service issues promptly.<br>Creates and maintains service reports. Plan and monitor the ongoing company presence on social media (Twitter, Facebook etc.)<br>Compile reports on overall customer satisfaction.<br>Launch optimized online adverts to increase company and brand awareness<br>Inform management about complex client issues and resolutions.<br>Maintain client focused working environment for team.<br>Work in compliance with company policies and procedures.<br>Identify and develop new business opportunities with client contacts.<br>Utilize effective problem solving and time management skills in client service operations.<br>Develop process improvements to enhance service efficiency and effectiveness.<br>Provide support in new product development and enhancement activities.<br><strong>Requirement</strong><br>Minimum of BSC in Social sciences, Mass communications or any other related discipline.<br><br>2-3 years experience as Customer service relationship or similar roles<br><br>Kindly send your CV to careers@homeandyoultd.com.ng and the position as the subject matter</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'careers@homeandyoultd.com.ng', '', 12, 'March 28, 2018'),
(101, 'Sale/Business Development', '', '', 'Vacancy for Resident Branch Controller, Merchant Acquisition & Payments Specialist and other positions at ACCION MICROFINANCE BANK', '', '<p>Resident Branch Controller, Merchant Acquisition &amp; Payments Specialist and other positions at ACCION MICROFINANCE BANK<br><br>Reports to: Head, Risk and Internal Control<br>Location: Ariaria, Abia State/Nnewi, Anambra State<br><br>Summary/Objective<br><br>Working in the employment of ACCION Microfinance Bank Limited, the employee will hold the Resident Branch Controller position with direct reporting line to Residence Control Manager. He shall be responsible for conceptual ownership of all management processes in operations within the branch(s) of the bank. He shall also ensure adequate compliance to information technology industry standards by the bank. He will identify potential risks inherent in the established procedures within these areas of his responsibility and Identify appropriate mitigating control measures against such risks. Where necessary control measures are not yet in place, the employee shall also have the responsibility to design appropriate controls for management approval and subsequent implementations. In this capacity the incumbent will be key support to the management and serves as the eye of the HOD, Internal Control and Compliance in ensuring all employees of the branch comply with laid down rules and procedures in the performance of the their assigned roles. In essence, his duties shall focus on ensuring the assets of the branch are safeguarded and ensuring the integrity of the branch records.<br><br>Job Duties and Responsibility<br>Ensure branch staff compliance with internal code of conduct, Policy/Procedure and Regulations.<br>Ensure that all activities as stipulated in the control checklist are performed by branch<br>Provide Control and Compliance Counseling, Advisory and Decision Support Service to branch<br>Educate and train staffs on compliance issues, Improve compliance culture in the assigned branch<br>Build strong KYC compliance environment in the assigned branch ie ensure capturing of all valid KYC documents in the core banking application through regular review of account opening and documentation both on clients files and on the system<br>Review credit files and escalate all risk observed.<br>Carryout unannounced visits to client&rsquo;s business location after loan disbursement.<br>Ensure daily call over of all Till transactions (which include but not limited to deposit/withdrawal slip, cheque slips, funds transfer) within 24hours of posting and where practicable online same day.<br>Daily review of ATM card and PIN management or any other related reviews to ensure irregularities are discovered and escalated promptly.<br>Ensure integrity of transactions and GL accounts in the branch through daily review of the branch GL balance report and escalate any major deviation from standard.<br>Ensure prompt resolution of all recommendations in internal audit report, regulatory examiners report and other statutory examiners report involving the branch under your purview<br>Conduct special investigation as maybe directed by the head Risk and Internal Control<br>Ensure prompt and qualitative rendition of relevant reports which include but not limited to Weekly Activity Report, Vault balancing Report, Downtime Report, Risk Event Report.<br>Any other job as assigned by the head Risk and Internal Control.<br>Qualification and Experience<br>Degrees &amp; Education<br>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or equivalent or specific relevant experience.<br>ICAN AAT, PE1 or ACA is an added advantage.<br>Knowledge &amp; Experience<br>Good Knowledge of risk management<br>Good knowledge of information technology is very important in order to interact with different applications, especially Microsoft tools.<br>Key Performance Measures<br>Control Adequacy rating from Internal Audit.<br>Promptness and effectiveness of call over of transactions.<br>Quantum of undetected regulatory/statutory infractions from External Auditor and Regulators&rsquo; reports.<br>Quality and Timeliness of losses and loss events reporting in processing areas<br>Undetected Income leakage/P&amp;L reversal arising from undetected processing errors<br>Integrity of the GL accounts in the Business offices of the region.<br>Promptness, Accuracy and Validity of Exception Reporting/Rendition of all Control Activity Reports<br>Effectiveness at follow up to ensure that Internal Audit recommendations are implemented<br>Click here to apply<br>http://accionmfb.com/Pages/Residence-Branch-Controller.aspx<br><br></p>', 'Abia', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 10, 'March 28, 2018'),
(102, 'Administration', '', '', 'NIGACHEM Nigeria Limited is hiring Human Resources Officer', '', '<p>NIGACHEM Nigeria Limited was incorporated in 1987 as a private company with Certificate of Incorporation No. 97718. The Company Memorandum and Articles of Association and subsequent licences permit the Company to engage in Importation, marketing and sales of Commercial or Civil Explosives and related products like Ammonium Nitrate, Detonating Cord, Electric Detonators, Non-Electric Detonators (Nonel), etc.<br><br>We are recruiting to fill the position below:<br><br>Job Title: Human Resources Manager<br><br>Location: Ikeja, Lagos<br><br><strong><em>Requirements</em></strong><br>HND/B.Sc. in any Social Sciences<br>A minimum of 5 years working experience<br>Ability to work with minimum or no supervision<br>Ability to work on any HR Softwares<br>Performance appraisal with good knowledge of KP1<br>Must be between the ages of 30-40 years<br>Application Closing Date<br>11th April, 2018.<br><br><strong><em>How to Apply</em></strong><br>Interested and qualified candidates should send their Application to:<br>The Advertiser,<br>P.O. Box 10749,<br>Ikeja,<br>Lagos State.<br>Or<br>Email: a.oyeniyi@nigachem.com.n g</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'a.oyeniyi@nigachem.com.n g', '', 12, 'March 28, 2018'),
(103, 'Administration', '', '', 'NIGACHEM Nigeria Limited is hiring Human Resources Officer', '', '<p>NIGACHEM Nigeria Limited was incorporated in 1987 as a private company with Certificate of Incorporation No. 97718. The Company Memorandum and Articles of Association and subsequent licences permit the Company to engage in Importation, marketing and sales of Commercial or Civil Explosives and related products like Ammonium Nitrate, Detonating Cord, Electric Detonators, Non-Electric Detonators (Nonel), etc.<br><br>We are recruiting to fill the position below:<br><br>Job Title: Human Resources Manager<br><br>Location: Ikeja, Lagos<br><br><strong><em>Requirements</em></strong><br>HND/B.Sc. in any Social Sciences<br>A minimum of 5 years working experience<br>Ability to work with minimum or no supervision<br>Ability to work on any HR Softwares<br>Performance appraisal with good knowledge of KP1<br>Must be between the ages of 30-40 years<br>Application Closing Date<br>11th April, 2018.<br><br><strong><em>How to Apply</em></strong><br>Interested and qualified candidates should send their Application to:<br>The Advertiser,<br>P.O. Box 10749,<br>Ikeja,<br>Lagos State.<br>Or<br>Email: a.oyeniyi@nigachem.com.n g</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'a.oyeniyi@nigachem.com.ng', '', 10, 'March 28, 2018'),
(104, 'Logistic/Transportation', '', '', 'Teefum Travels and Tours Limited is recruiting to fill the position of a Ticketing and Reservations Officer', '', '<p>Teefum Travels and Tours Limited is recruiting to fill the position of a Ticketing and Reservations Officer</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br>Location: Abuja<br>Application Closing Date<br>20th April, 2018.<br><br>Send CV to: jobs@teefumtravels.com with the subject &quot;Application for Ticketing and Reservations Officer&quot;</p>', 'Abuja', '', 'jobs@teefumtravels.com', '', 16, 'March 28, 2018'),
(105, 'Hotel', '', '', 'RESTAURANT MANAGER, WAITERS AND CHEF POSITIONS AT IBADAN', '', '<p><strong><em>WAITRESS / WAITER POSITION</em></strong><br>We are looking for a skilled Waiter or Waitress to take orders and deliver food and beverages to our customers.<br>The right Waiter/Waitress uplifts the dining experience for customers. We are looking for someone who will have the patience, personality and perseverance to thrive in this role.<br>Ultimately, it is the duty of our Waiters/Waitresses to provide an excellent overall dining experience for our guests.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>&bull;Greet and escort customers to their tables<br>&bull;Present menu and provide detailed information when asked (e.g. about portions, ingredients or potential food allergies)<br>&bull;Prepare tables by setting up linens, silverware and glasses<br>&bull;Inform customers about the day&rsquo;s specials<br>&bull;Offer menu recommendations upon request<br>&bull;Up-sell additional products when appropriate<br>&bull;Take customers&rsquo; orders<br>&bull;Communicate order details to the Kitchen Staff<br>&bull;Serve food and drink orders<br>&bull;Check dishes and kitchenware for cleanliness, present and report any issues<br>&bull;Arrange table settings and maintain a tidy dining area<br>&bull;Deliver checks and collect bill payments<br>&bull;Carry dirty plates, glasses and silverware for cleaning<br>&bull;Meet with restaurant staff to review daily specials, changes on the menu and service specifications for reservations (e.g. parties)<br>&bull;Provide excellent customer service to guests<br><br>Requirements<br>&bull;Minimum of HND in any related discipline<br>&bull;Proven work experience as a Waiter/Waitress<br>&bull;Hands-on experience with cash register and ordering information system<br>&bull;Basic math skills<br>&bull;Attentiveness and patience for customers<br>&bull;Excellent presentation skills<br>&bull;Strong organizational and multitasking skills, with the ability to perform well in a fast-paced environment<br>&bull;Active listening and effective communication skills<br>&bull;Team spirit<br>&bull;Flexibility to work in shifts<br>&bull;High school diploma; food safety training is a plus<br><br><strong><em>RESTAURANT MANAGER</em></strong><br>We are looking for a Restaurant Manager to oversee all aspects of our business. He/She will deliver high quality menu and motivate our staff to provide excellent customer service.<br><br>Responsibilities<br>&bull;Coordinate daily front-end and back-end activities of the restaurant operations<br>&bull;Deliver superior service and maximize customer satisfaction<br>&bull;Respond efficiently and accurately to customer complaints<br>&bull;Regularly review product quality and research new vendors<br>&bull;Organize and supervise shifts<br>&bull;Appraise staff performance and provide feedback to improve productivity<br>&bull;Estimate future needs for goods, kitchen utensils and cleaning products<br>&bull;Ensure compliance with sanitation and safety regulations<br>&bull;Manage restaurant&rsquo;s good image and suggest ways to improve it<br>&bull;Control operational costs and identify measures to cut waste<br><br>Requirements<br>&bull;BA degree in Business Administration; Accounting, Hospitality Management or any related discipline<br>&bull;Minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience in restaurant management, or any management position<br>&bull;Proven work experience as a Restaurant Manager, Restaurant General Manager/Hospitality Management or similar role<br>&bull;Proven customer service experience as a manager<br>&bull;Strong leadership, motivational and people skills<br>&bull;Acute financial management skills<br><br><strong><em>CHEF</em></strong><br>Responsibilities<br>&bull;Set up the kitchen with cooking utensils and equipment<br>&bull;Study each recipe and gather all necessary ingredients<br>&bull;Cook in a timely manner<br>&bull;Delegate tasks to the kitchen staff<br>&bull;Inform waiters/waitresses about daily specials<br>&bull;Ensure appealing plate presentation<br>&bull;Supervise Cooks and assist when needed<br>&bull;Slightly modify recipes to meet customers&rsquo; needs and requests (e.g. reduce salt, remove dairy)<br>&bull;Monitor food stocks and place orders<br>&bull;Check freshness of food and discard out-of-date items<br>&bull;Experiment with recipes and suggest new ingredients<br>&bull;Ensure compliance with all health and safety regulations within the kitchen area<br><br>Requirements<br>&bull;Minimum of HND in any related field with experience in Culinary skills<br>&bull;Proven work experience as a Chef or cook<br>&bull;Hands-on experience with various kitchen equipment (e.g. grillers and pasta makers)<br>&bull;Advanced knowledge of culinary, baking and pastry techniques<br>&bull;Leadership skills<br>&bull;Ability to remain calm and multitask<br>&bull;Excellent time management abilities<br>&bull;Up-to-date knowledge of cooking techniques and recipes<br>&bull;Familiar with sanitation regulations<br>&bull;Culinary school diploma preferred<br><br>Location: Ibadan, Oyo State<br><br>Application Details<br>CVs and Application Letters should be forwarded to humanenergisers@gmail.com</p>', 'Ibadan', '', 'humanenergisers@gmail.com', '', 32, 'March 28, 2018'),
(106, 'Marketing', '', '', 'Fresh Jobs in Ilorin, Interview is Wednesday April 4th, 2018', '', '<p><br>We are in urgent need of HND/BSc graduates&nbsp;</p><p><strong><em> *Sales Executives position* </em></strong>(Presellers)<br><br>Candidate must reside in Ilorin<br><br>Work location: Ilorin<br><br>Pay is 70-75k.<br><br>Interested and qualified candidates should be at the assessment venue on Wednesday April 4, 2018 by 12pm.<br><br>Assessment Venue: Comfort Conference Hall, 1 Adelodun Road, Flower Garden GRA Ilorin.<br><br>Kindly come along with your CV, credentials and a p!assport.<br><br>For more information contact 08188800444</p>', 'Ilorin ', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 83, 'April 01, 2018'),
(107, 'Medicals', '', '', 'UK need Nurses from Common Wealth countries', '', '<p>UK needs Nurses from commonwealth countries<br><br>Are you, or do you know of a Qualified Nurse with two years minimum experience in a commonwealth country who wish to relocate with family and work in the UK?<br><br>Click https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/uk-visas-and-immigration to go to the home office website or Contact me or the UK Visa center for details<br><br>Tel: +44 7404 213 364<br>Off: +44 2032 391 228<br>Em: admin@uvc.legal<br><br>Registration begins on 1 April 18 for those wishing to migrate from 3 Sept 18<br><br>UK visa center is registered and regulated by the OISC in the UK</p>', 'Nigeria', '', 'admin@uvc.legal', '', 11, 'April 03, 2018'),
(108, 'Teaching', '', '', 'Experienced class teachers, clerk, Gardner at ADEROJU MODEL SCHOOL, ILORIN', '', '<p>VACANCIES<br>@ a reputable PRIMARY/SECONDARY SCHOOL.<br><br>Due to the positive growth and the development of our school in general, we&nbsp;hereby invite applicants for the following positions:<br><br>1. Experienced Class Teachers (Education Qualifications such NCE, B.Ed, PGDE etc are additional advantages)<br>2. Qualified and Experienced NURSES.<br>3. An experienced Clerk (Knowledge of graphic design is strongly recommended)<br>4. A librarian<br>5. An experienced Gardener<br><br>Interested candidates should submit CVs and applications at ADEROJU MODEL SCHOOL, Aderoju Sagaya road, Off Awolowo road Tanke, Ilorin.<br><br><br></p>', 'Ilorin ', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 22, 'April 05, 2018'),
(109, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for Human resources officer at Richbrands group', '', '<p>Richbrands Group is an uncommon marketing communications enterprise with the primary purpose of helping brands grow. We achieve this by deploying the most effective communication to the consumer or target audience using our unique, creative and unboxed ideas, strategies and tactics. We are big on the application of technological tools to boost the accuracy, efficiency and effectiveness of our results.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title: Human Resource Officer/Admin Officer&nbsp;<br><br>Location:</strong> Lagos</p><p><strong><br>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Recruiting, training and developing staff.</li><li>Approving job descriptions and advertisements.</li><li>Looking after the health, safety and welfare of all employees</li><li>Organising staff training sessions and activities.</li><li>Supervises the work of employees in supporting roles, including assigning workload and monitoring staff performance and attendance.</li><li>Advising line managers and other employees on employment law and the employer&#39;s own employment policies and procedures.</li><li>Ensuring candidates have the right to work at the organization.</li><li>Negotiating salaries, contracts, working conditions or redundancy packages with staff and representatives.</li><li>Conduct and coordinate the recruitment/ selection process including advertising position openings, screening applications, short listing candidate, preparing assessment (test and interviews), defining selection criteria, notifying applicant of selection outcome, conducting employment reference checks and addressing concerns applicants may have about the selection process.</li><li>Perform professional human resources services which include benefits administration, recruitment/selection, performance reviews, employee relations, training management.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement and Experience</strong></p><ul><li>At least first degree Degree in any Discipline.</li><li>Masters in Human Resources Management will be an added advantage.</li><li>Professional qualification in HR is an added advantage.</li><li>Must be 28 years and Above.</li><li>Minimum of 2-7 years working experience as an Human Resource Officer.</li></ul><p>Required Skills:</p><ul><li>Strategic Planning &amp; Management</li><li>Leadership &amp; Administration</li><li>Change Management</li><li>Relationship Management</li><li>Strong analytical and project management skills.</li><li>Critical Thinking</li><li>Communication</li><li>Coaching</li><li>Confident and dynamic personality.</li><li>Strong creative outlook.</li><li>Must know to how drive and possess a Driver&#39;s License.</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date&nbsp;</strong></p><p>11th April, 2018.&nbsp;</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should send their CVs to:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com" target="_blank"><strong>recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com</strong></a></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com', '', 4, 'April 06, 2018'),
(110, 'Administration', '', '', 'Vacancy for content writer intern at Richbrands group', '', '<p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>Richbrands Group is an uncommon marketing communications enterprise with the primary purpose of helping brands grow. We achieve this by deploying the most effective communication to the consumer or target audience using our unique, creative and unboxed ideas, strategies and tactics. We are big on the application of technological tools to boost the accuracy, efficiency and effectiveness of our results.</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p>We are recruiting to fill the position below:&nbsp;</p><p data-empty="true"><br></p><p><strong>Job Title:&nbsp;</strong><strong>Content Writer Intern<br><br>Location</strong>: Lagos</p><p><strong><br>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Excellent overall writing skills in a number of different styles/tones</li><li>Impeccable spelling and grammar</li><li>A deep understanding of consumers and what motivates them online</li><li>Great research, organizational, and learning skills</li><li>High comprehension of software like Microsoft Word and Google Docs</li><li>Familiarity with keyword placement and other SEO best practices</li><li>Some experience with online marketing and lead generation</li><li>An understanding of formatting articles on the web</li><li>Additionally, must be a passionate learners since you will be writing about a variety of topics and types of businesses. Their ability to take complex information and turn it into easy-to-understand copy is an essential aspect of any project.</li></ul><p><strong>Application Closing Date</strong></p><p>21st April, 2018.</p><p><strong><br>Method of Application</strong></p><p>Interested and qualified candidates should send their CV&#39;s to:&nbsp;<a href="mailto:recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com" target="_blank"><strong>recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com</strong></a> using the job title as subject of the email.</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'recruitment@richbrandsgroup.com', '', 6, 'April 06, 2018'),
(111, 'Pharmaceutical', '', '', 'Vacancy for Pharmacists at Cikason Pharmaceuticals', '', '<p>Our Client, Cikason Pharmaceuticals is a pharmaceutical store into wholesales distribution and supply of medicines and hospital equipment. We require the service of a &nbsp;Young Pharmacist to take charge of and direct the &nbsp;Sales and Marketing activities of the company.<br><br><strong><em>Requirements</em></strong><br>1. Must be a Young Pharmacist (Preferably young graduate pharmacist presently serving as a National Youth Corps Member in Lagos State).<br><br>2. &lrm;Have sales experience.<br><br>3. &lrm;Must be able to work without supervision as tasks might often require this.<br><br>4.Must be a good communicator.<br><br>Your mail should have the subject Application for the position of a Sales Personnel for Cikason Pharmaceuticals<br><br>If interested, please send your CV to compliance@hexavia.net on or before the close of work on Wednesday 11/04/2018.<br><br><br></p>', 'Lagos', '', 'compliance@hexavia.net', '', 5, 'April 09, 2018'),
(112, 'Call Centre', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of Customer Service', '', '<p>Do you have any one who is interested in the position of a Customer service Officer?&nbsp;</p><p>Recruitment is on going</p><p>Interested candidates should come to</p><p>5, Ogbunike Str, off Admiralty way , Lekki phase 1, Lagos</p><p><br></p><p>Time :11am</p><p>Interview continue to Wednesday</p><p>For more information, call +2348188000800</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 6, 'April 09, 2018'),
(113, 'Accounting', '', '', 'Vacancy for the position of Accountant', '', '<p><br><br>Competencies</p><p>Great numeracy ability,&nbsp;</p><p>Highly proficient with Microsoft excel,&nbsp;</p><p>Great organizational ability.</p><p><br></p><p><br>Experience level: 1 - 2 years experience.</p><p><br>Preferred qualification: BSc in financial accounting or economics or any relevant field<br><br>Qualified candidates should send cvs to: recruitment@alaralagos.com<br>&nbsp;</p>', 'Lagos', '', 'myhotjbz@gmail.com', '', 10, 'April 09, 2018'),
(114, 'Teaching', '', '', 'Fresh Jobs at Rehoboth Kiddies, Ilorin', '', '<p>Rehoboth College, Pipeline is one of the growing secondary schools in Ilorin. It had recently kicked off its Primary section &#39;REHOBOTH KIDDIES&#39;.</p><p>Highly motivated and experienced teachers are urgently needed</p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY</strong></p><p><strong>A</strong>pply in the school premises, along pipeline road with your CV and cover letter</p>', 'Ilorin ', '', 'myhotjobz@gmail.com', '', 15, 'April 10, 2018');
